	<item>
				<title>23snaps Mom Bloggers Directory</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-mom-bloggers-directory/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 22 Feb 2013 16:31:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740093708</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Are you a mom blogger that uses 23snaps? Why not write a review or add our badge to your blog sidebar to get included in our Mom Blog Directory below?

It's simple to join, gets your blog in front of tens of thousands of 23snaps users and means you're the first to hear about new 23snaps features - you'll even get free codes to try out 23snaps offerings like photo printing and photo books. Plus, our staff select posts from the 23snaps Mom Blog Directory to feature on our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/23snaps">Facebook Page</a> with over 11,000 followers!

To get added to the directory, simply add the badge, below, to your blog's sidebar or write a review about your experience using 23snaps. Send the link, along with your name, Twitter username and Facebook page URL to <a href="mailto:lucy@23snaps.com">lucy(at)23snaps(d0t)com</a> and you'll be added within 24 hours. It's that simple!

<td style="float: right; width: 440px;"><b>Copy and paste the HTML code below to add the badge to your blog:</b><form action="" method="post">
<a title="23snaps - Private Photo Sharing for Families" href="http://www.23snaps.com" target="blank"><img title="23snaps - Private Photo Sharing for Families" alt="23snaps - Private Photo Sharing for Families" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/snapper-badge1.png" /></a>

</form></td>

&nbsp;

<hr />

Members of the 23snaps Street Team volunteer their knowledge and time to inspire other users and spread the word about 23snaps - but being a member of the 23snaps Street Team comes with a load of great benefits including:

<img style="float: left; width: 100px; padding: 10px;" alt="" src="http://www.mobileapptesting.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/Beta-Testing-247x300.jpg" /><strong>Early Access to New 23snaps Features</strong>

Street Team members get exclusive access to a private version of the app that includes new features as we build and test them for release. They also get to add their input to the development process and influence which new features we add next.

&nbsp;

<img style="float: left; width: 100px; padding: 10px;" alt="" src="http://d2pbvzqv6ybw6u.cloudfront.net/version/2557/assets/images/products/240/hcl_product_023865.jpg" /><strong>Free 23snaps Photobook Subscription</strong>

Every three months, Street Team members get an extra-special delivery: a photo book with all of the photos they've added to 23snaps since their last book!

&nbsp;

<img style="float: left; width: 100px; padding: 10px;" alt="" src="http://dev.suffolkbreakthroughevents.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/lunch-parties-main.jpg" /><strong>Invites to Exclusive 23snaps Events
</strong>
Meet other Street Team members at the 23snaps staff at private 23snaps lunches and events for a chance to get to know the team and relax with (or without) the kids.

&nbsp;

<img style="float: left; width: 100px; padding: 10px;" alt="" src="http://mgoblog.com/sites/mgoblog.com/files/ThingsThatHappenedDuringTheGreatMalwareD_13A1C/Surprise.jpg" /><strong>And more!
</strong>
We like to send thank yous to our Street Team members - after all they are the 23snaps experts who have helped us make the app even better for their families and ours!

&nbsp;

Think you'd like to apply to join the 23snaps Street Team? Email <a href="mailto:meaghan@23snaps.com">meaghan@23snaps.com</a> telling us why you are a 23snaps expert!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Zoe O&#039;Shea &#124; 23snaps Street Team</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-street-team/zoe-oshea-23snaps-street-team/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2013 16:02:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740094628</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094629" style="margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;" alt="23 snaps" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23-snaps-730x1024.jpg" width="230" height="323" />My name is Zoé. I am currently on maternity leave and enjoying watching my daughter grow!

I love my many hobbies including gardening and hospital radio. I started using 23Snaps just a couple of weeks after she was born, I was looking for a social media app that allowed me to share photos of my daughter with close friends and family but that meant that the photos were private. 23Snaps was the best fit.

I was really pleased with the way that it worked and it means that not only have I been able to update friends and family from near and far, keeping them as a big part of my daughter's life, I have also been able to keep a scrapbook of her life for myself. Time passes so quickly; you think you will remember things but you don't, I can look back through the months and see how much she has grown and enjoy such happy memories.

<strong>My top tips for 23snaps:</strong>

<strong>- Download the app onto all of your devices</strong> and post photos as soon as you can, its so quick and easy. When you have the app on your Android, iPad or husbands iPhone you can upload photos very quickly and friends and family can see what your child is up to!

<strong>- Encourage your partner and family to use the app</strong> to upload photos too, when you go out without your child it can be hard but seeing the photos of what they have been doing means that you can share in their day.

<strong>- Snap away freely</strong> to create the best photos.

<strong>- Use the editing tools.</strong> Always remember to crop your image, this ensures that you post only the cute photo of your baby and the used nappy/talcum powder/other mess is not seen, just you child's beautiful grin.]]></content:encoded>

				<title>Steve Berrick &#124; 23snaps Street Team</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-street-team/steve-berrick-23snaps-street-team/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 10:58:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740094962</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-39740094965" style="margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;" alt="IMG_2215" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/IMG_2215-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /> Hi, I'm Steve and I'm a geek dad. I'm also an artist, a creative coder and an educator. My work is diverse; I've toured internationally performing interactive installations engaging crowds of people, and I currently work weekends at the National Gallery of Australia doing creative activities with families.

Since the beginning of 2012 I've taken up the role of stay-at-home dad to my now two year old son Cabe... and I love it. Watching Cabe discover the world is helping me rediscover it, and my artistic practice is being informed in ways I could never have foreseen. In turn I build him quirky iPad apps and strange electronic musical instruments to fuel his geeky curiosities.

&nbsp;

You can follow me around at:

twitter: @grivvr
instagram: @grivvr
tumblr: <a href="http://grivvr.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">grivvr.tumblr.com</a>

Here's a few of <em><strong>my tips</strong></em> on maximising your 23Snaps experience:

<em><strong>Moments are short.</strong></em>
I predominantly use the native iPhone camera app because I can launch it quickly from the lock screen straight out of my pocket. I shoot as many photos as I can in the hope of catching one great moment.

<em><strong>Post daily.</strong></em>
Sometimes it feels like a struggle to find a good photo for the day, but it's worth it when you look back on them months or years later. Every photo will reveal something interesting about your child in retrospect.

<em><strong>Collections.</strong></em>
Collection are great for grouping photos. We have about a dozen collections, such as "with Dad", "with friends" and "with Cousins". We also use collections for events like "little brother's wedding holiday". It makes browsing photos with the grandparents around the Christmas table really easy.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Leyla Brooke &#124; 23snaps Street Team</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-street-team/leyla-brooke-23snaps-street-team/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 09:47:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740095020</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095022" style="margin: 5px; float: left;" alt="NEO_0351" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/NEO_0351.jpg" width="300" height="214" />
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;">Hi, I am Leyla a full time working Mum to two beautiful girls and a full time blogger at <a href="http://www.thisdayilove.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.thisdayilove.co.uk</a>.  Juggling family life, blog and work can be tricky at times but some how it all gets done.  My girls are 1 and 3 and so life is always fun and interesting.  Having the phone ready to capture those precious moments and then writing them on my blog so I can remember a positive from each day.</span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;"> </span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;">23snaps has given me a great platform to share the girls growing up over a secure and private media.  Our family are in most corners of the world and I can use 23snaps to keep up to date with them.  </span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;"> </span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;">My top tips are:</span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;"> </span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;"><strong>1. Download 23snaps onto different devices</strong>.  I have the app on my phone, as does my husband.  It means we can upload any where any time, and we are not sat waiting for the internet or the one device that contains the only version.  This makes it fast easy and convenient to use.</span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;"> </span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;"><strong>2. I prefer to bulk update.</strong>  I get all the pictures together in one place ready to upload.  I am then not looking for photos and I know that all the ones I want to upload are uploaded.  I don;t forget any that way.,</span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;"> </span></div>
<div><span style="color: #565752; font-family: Arial;"><strong>3. Update regularly.</strong>  Family like to share those moments as soon as possible to when they happen, and don't forget to print some off too for keepsakes.</span></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Aug 2013 13:53:47 +0000</pubDate>

	<item>
				<title>Christina Jones &#124; 23snaps Street Team</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-street-team/christina-jones-23snaps-street-team/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Aug 2013 13:46:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740095273</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/891840_10101710767435191_244107685_o.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-39740095274" style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="891840_10101710767435191_244107685_o" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/891840_10101710767435191_244107685_o.jpg" width="271" height="347" /></a>Hi! I'm Christina, mom to a rambunctious little boy. I currently work as a freelancer and run my own tech parenting blog, <a href="http://techchicmom.com/" target="_blank">Tech Chic Mom</a>. As a Gen Y mom and working professional, it can often be a challenge to find a work/life balance. What I love about tech is there is a way to find that balance.</div>
&nbsp;
<div>That's what I love about 23snaps. I'm able to share photos of my son with family whether they're in the same city or across the country. They are able to keep up with his milestones and watch him grow. It's also a great way to share fun family moments that you may not want to share with your followers on other platforms.</div>
<div><em><strong>A few tips for users:</strong></em></div>
<b>- Get funky with the filters!</b> The app has great filters, and they add such a special touch to each photo.

<b>- Remind family members to use the app when you've updated it with new photos.</b> Sometimes a family member will text or call me to send a photo or video of my son so they can see how he's growing up. It's so much easier now to tell them to check out the app or send me their email address so I can send them an invite.

<b>- Don't forget to caption your photos.</b> It adds even more personality to each photo, and lets family and friends know what's going on in the photo and how you were feeling at the time.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Alison Duveen &#124; 23snaps Street Team</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-street-team/alison-duveen-23snaps-street-team/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Aug 2013 15:43:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740095294</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Alison-Duveen.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-39740095299" style="margin-right: 15px;" alt="Alison Duveen" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Alison-Duveen-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a>Hello lovelies!  I'm Alison, a South African expat who has been living in the UK for going on 9 years this October.  By day I run a marketing business, and when I'm not in the office, I am a full time mom to my beautiful daughter and wife to my long suffering husband.  I also have a blog, <a href="http://all-in-onemum.blogspot.co.uk">All in One Mum</a>, and sell Virgin Wines in my spare time!

With everything that I do, my free time is incredibly precious to me.  I like to make the most of every second I have with my family, hence the fact that I have thousands of images of my daughter, taken almost every day since her birth three years ago.  Surprisingly, I only have a few pictures of myself?  My husband, who hates his photo taken, has more than me?  Need to work on that...

As most of my family and close friends live back in Cape Town, I needed a way of sharing my images of my daughter with them on a secure platform that they could all readily access.  23snaps is just that; it's fabulously easy to use and even my mom uses it to send me pictures of her children aka her dogs.

I recommend this app to all new parents that I meet, and to grandparents too.  The fact that they don't really know me doesn't bother me at all.  I like to think that I'm helping them in the long run and that they thanked me silently for sharing this wonderful app with them after they've used it.

If I had to give my top three tips, they would be....

1.  <b>Get all your family in on the deal.</b>  My husband, parents, in-laws, sister and good friends all use the app in some way, shape or form.  Being in different countries, we using different systems such as Android phones, iPhones, Mac, PC, iPad and other tablets.  It works across all of them so they have no excuse not to see my gorgeous child and leave a comment and then share their images too.

2.  <b>All pictures are perfect! </b> There are no good or bad pictures.  Even if it was slightly blurred or there was a tiny finger across the lense, that picture captured that moment in time perfectly, so share it!

3.  <b>Update regularly and if you can't, update when you can!</b>  I love that all the images fall naturally into the correct space on the timeline, so when I don't upload immediately or if I do things in reverse order, 23snaps automagically fits them in where they need to go.  Updating regularly means you don't need to upload in bulk, which some people prefer, but I like to do single uploads.

Happy snapping and sharing!

A x]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Charlotte&#039;s Story</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740096470</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740096470</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-39740096477" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/photo-1-3.png" alt="photo 1 (3)" width="300" /></td>
<td><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-39740096479" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/photo-3.png" alt="photo 3" width="300" /></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<blockquote>On March 18th, 2013 my daughter Charlotte was born. My husband Ben and I were elated and so in love, but it was a very stressful time. Due to pre eclampsia, she was delivered by C section at 31 weeks gestation. Charlotte weighed two pounds, eight ounces at birth and was 39 centimeters long. She needed respiratory aid, a central line into her belly button and an IV. She was admitted to the NICU where she spent over eight long weeks before coming home.

I first read about <a href="http://www.23snaps.com">23snaps</a> in Canadian Living magazine while on bed rest in hospital. It appealed to me because Ben and I have family and friends across the globe and we would want to share regular updates of our little one once the baby arrived. I downloaded the app right away then promptly forgot about it when Charlotte arrived so suddenly.

<center><img class="alignnone" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/quote3.png" alt="" width="440" /></center>
About a week after Charlotte was born I was discharged and having to leave my fragile baby at the hospital at the end of the day was heart wrenching. It was then that I first turned to 23snaps as a way to share our sweet little one with the world she had been born into. Immediately the response we got were overwhelming, all our family felt really involved and to this day, my aunt in Scotland talks about the magic of the 23snaps app and how it helped her feel connected to us during the anxious time.

When you have a baby in critical care you are beyond exhausted and emotional. However, 23snaps was a light at the end of my long day at the hospital. I would choose a photo from the day to post and know that our loved ones were sharing in Charlotte's journey and growth. To be honest it kept a few of our relatives quiet, in the sense that they weren't calling or emailing all the time for updates because I was posted growth information and photos on 23snaps. That was a huge relief for us. We loved reading the comments posted. Often I would reread them while sitting near to Charlotte's incubator during the day and smile.

<center><img class="alignnone" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/quote.png" alt="" width="440" /></center>In a sense 23snaps helped me feel in control of the hospital experience. When recently looked back on the photos I picked to add to our timeline, I was surprised. I thought I had only chosen happy photos, but I realized there were some that had been taken on difficult days, such as when Charlotte had a setback and had to move from her hospital crib back into an incubator. I think being able to share the good and bad stories was therapeutic and healing for me.

Charlotte is now a healthy, happy one year old. We continue to use 23snaps, I think if we stopped there would be an outcry from our family! I know that someday, sooner than I am ready to admit, Charlotte will ask to see what I'm doing and I will show her the timeline of photos. We will look through every one and talk about how far she has come, how brave she was and how she inspires a lot of people around the world. And she will say, "wow", as she does so well, about the concept of 23snaps.</blockquote>
<em>23snaps is completely private and secure. No photos, videos or stories are shared publicly unless the author chooses. This content has been created expressly to share Charlotte's story and how 23snaps helped her family.</em>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>There is no such thing as too much feedback</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/24366093573/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 03 Jun 2012 23:36:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/24366093573</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>One of the most exciting things about being live with 23snaps has been the feedback from our users. It is obvious that people are very passionate about this topic and we love hearing everyone&#8217;s thoughts and ideas.</p>
<p align="center"><img align="middle" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m52dnxI2bO1rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/>
<p>Being a young technology company means that we get to work closely with our users and act on ideas and suggestions to improve the product for everyone. We naturally can&#8217;t build every single feature requests, however there will be functionality that we have not thought about. If there is anything that bothers you or would make the app that much better for you, please do get in touch, we are always listening and love hearing your feedback - positive or negative.</p>
<p>You can email us at feedback at 23snaps.com</p>
<p>You can tweets us at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/23snaps" title="23snaps twitter" target="_blank">@23snaps</a></p>
<p>23snaps is only days old, so there are a few bugs in the app, which we are very actively fixing as we go, but if you notice anything drop us a line too.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>No iPhone, No Problem</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/24471684285/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 05 Jun 2012 14:39:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/24471684285</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>One of the most common questions that we have been hearing over the last few days has been along the lines of:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>I&#8217;d like to share my daughter&#8217;s moments with my mother, but she doesn&#8217;t have an iPhone. What should I do?</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>The answer to this question is simple. You can invite people that do not have an iPhone to connect with you on 23snaps. When they receive an invitation, they can click through to the website, accept the invite and subscribe to an email digest of everything that you post.</p>
<p>What is an email digest? It is a summary of everything that you have shared over a selected period of time, packaged up in an email and delivered straight to their inbox. It comes with one guarantee, to make them smile! Below is an example of what it would look like.</p>
<p align="center"><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m55ghppMI11rqaa0a.png" alt=""/>
<p>Not only they can subscribe to the digest, but they can also set how often they wish to receive it. Currently the available options are:</p>
<p><strong>As it happens</strong> - This option is for people that want to feel that they are there at all times. It will send them an email the second a new moment is shared.</p>
<p><strong>Daily</strong> - This option is for the busy people, who like to see and enjoy everything at the end of the day. This setting will send a daily email containing all of the shared moments for the day.</p>
<p><strong>Weekly</strong> - This option is for the people that like to save the best for last and enjoy a full collection at the end of a busy week. This setting will send a weekly email containing all of the shared moments for the week.</p>
<p>We are working on many more ways to share everything with the people you love and will be bringing them out soon, so watch this space.</p>
<p>To get updates on whats new on 23snaps follow <a href="http://www.twitter.com/23snaps" target="_blank">@23snaps</a> on twitter.</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

				<title>Online storage systems - how secure are they?</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094454</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094454</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740094455" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094455">
<img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-39740094455" alt="23snaps; online storage - how secure is it?" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-online-storage-how-secure-is-it-1024x352.jpg" width="640" height="220" /></a>

When you choose to upload you photos to the internet, be it via 23snaps, Dropbox, Facebook or any other service that can store digital photos, the level of security afforded to your files depends on the transfer and storage encryption techniques used. These techniques vary depending on the service you're using, but a <em><strong>secure</strong></em> online storage system is likely to use the following process. Before your files even leave your device they are encoded using SSL encryption technology, this is a protocol developed for transmitting private documents via the internet.

The files are then uploaded when the client (you) and the server have established a secure connection, your photos would be sent to your storage service via an SSL connection that will prevent other people from spying on, or interrupting, your data during the upload process.

Finally, when your photos reach their destination a 3rd layer of protection is added using a another series of algorithms to encrypt your files, this would then guarantee maximum protection for your files.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740094458" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094458"><img class="alignright  wp-image-39740094458" style="margin: 0px 20px;" alt="galaxys3" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/galaxys3.jpg" width="254" height="481" /></a>We want to assure you that is you have chosen to post photos to 23snaps, all of your content is uploaded to our secure storage servers, which are part of the Amazon S3 server network. Amazon is highly regarded for reliability and security in data storage and their S3 servers are used by companies including NASDAQ, Ticketmaster and Amazon themselves. We send the digital data to these servers using a secured connection and all of our data processing meets the minimum requirements for sites cleared to handle credit card transactions or financial data, meaning we use the same kinds of secure technology as your online banking system might.

Hopefully you now have a better understanding of how your files are stored, it's important that you don't just assume your files are safe, a little research is always recommended. Also, thanks for giving us the opportunity to reiterate how seriously we take privacy and the needs of families. 23snaps is built by parents, for parents and for our own families because the existing photo sharing services didn't offer the privacy and family-focused features we felt were required. Photos of our own children and loved ones are all stored in 23snaps. Our privacy terms are there to protect all of our users, including ourselves.]]></content:encoded>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740096615"><em>September, 2014 - </em><strong>23snaps launches Windows Phone App</strong></a>

<a href="https://23snaps.com">23snaps</a>, the private photo sharing network for families, has just achieved another milestone on its mission to become the most accessible family photo journal app for parents. This week, the service launched their version of the app for Windows Phone, which has a whole new layout specially designed for the platform. <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740096615">Read more...</a>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740096612"><em>July, 2014 - </em><strong>23snaps’ Stories are changing the way people share content online</strong></a>

<a href="http://www.23snaps.com">23snaps'</a> Stories, a new approach to sharing content in context, have quickly become the favored format for content consumption among 23snaps' 500,000 strong user base.

In March 2014, the family-focused photo sharing app 23snaps announced the release of Stories. Stories enable the families on 23snaps to benefit from a more versatile method of sharing memories and experiences. <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740096612">Read more...</a>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-media-center/private-family-focused-social-network-23snaps-becomes-the-first-social-network-to-allow-users-to-create-and-share-multimedia-stories-in-their-news-feed/"><em>March, 2014 - </em><strong>Private family-focused social network 23snaps becomes the first social network to allow users to create and share multimedia stories in their news feed</strong></a>

Today <a href="http://www.23snaps.com/" target="_blank">23snaps</a>, the private social network for families, announce the launch of Stories. Stories are a brand new type of content for social networks that allow users to quickly and easily combine photos, videos and text into beautiful multimedia vignettes and post them to their news feed alongside traditional photo or status updates. <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-media-center/private-family-focused-social-network-23snaps-becomes-the-first-social-network-to-allow-users-to-create-and-share-multimedia-stories-in-their-news-feed/">Read more...</a>

23snaps the mobile-first private social network for families announces today an expansion to their partnership program that in 2013 welcomed consumer electronics manufacturer Pix-Star and printing-on-demand service Peecho among others. <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-media-center/23snaps-partnership-program-grows-creating-new-opportunities-to-connect-with-families-and-consumers-around-the-world/">Read more...</a>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps partnership program grows, creating new opportunities to connect with families and consumers around the world.</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-media-center/23snaps-partnership-program-grows-creating-new-opportunities-to-connect-with-families-and-consumers-around-the-world/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 23 Jan 2014 15:11:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740096360</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>23 January, 2014 London, UK</em> - <a href="http://www.23snaps.com">23snaps</a> the mobile-first private social network for families announces today an expansion to their partnership program that in 2013 welcomed consumer electronics manufacturer <a href="http://www.pix-star.com">Pix-Star</a> and printing-on-demand service <a href="http://www.peecho.com">Peecho</a> among others.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">The 23snaps partnership program offers companies that share 23snaps’ focus on secure and simple family-focused technology the opportunity to co-develop products and features aimed at making family sharing easier and more enjoyable, and to connect with over half a million families around the world.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">23snaps head of marketing Meaghan Fitzgerald, says “Last year allowed us to trial partnerships with a small number of hand-selected companies and services. We’ve had such a fantastic response from both partners and users, and we look forward to working with an even broader range of partners in 2014.”</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Since its launch in June 2012, 23snaps has seen 20% month on month growth, surpassing 500,000 registered users. Over 6 million photos, videos and updates have been added to the platform and a new update is uploaded to 23snaps every second.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Whole families across the globe privately share photos online with 23snaps; whether on a phone, a tablet or a computer. The easy-to- use app aims to help parents “capture, share and cherish every special moment of their children’s lives” and order photo prints and books of their favorite memories directly from the app or website.</p>

<em>More about 23snaps</em>

<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>23snaps is a mobile-first private social network for families that allows parents to save photos, videos and stories of their children to a beautiful digital album and privately share those updates with family and close friends around the world. Founded by Ivailo Jordanov and Yury Tereshchenko, 23snaps launched in June, 2012 and has since attracted over half a million users in 179 countries. 23snaps has won a Lovie Award for Best Lifestyle App, selected as a top App for Parents in the Loved by Parents awards, and is featured regularly in the App Store, Play Store and Windows App Store.</em></p>

<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>23snaps is available for free on the iPhone, iPad, Android, Windows 8 and Web www.23snaps.com and drives revenues through the sales of photo prints and photo books.</em></p>

&nbsp;

	<item>
				<title>Private family-focused social network 23snaps becomes the first social network to allow users to create and share multimedia stories in their news feed</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-media-center/private-family-focused-social-network-23snaps-becomes-the-first-social-network-to-allow-users-to-create-and-share-multimedia-stories-in-their-news-feed/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 17 Mar 2014 11:57:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740096413</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">Today <a href="http://www.23snaps.com/" target="_blank">23snaps</a>, the private social network for families, announce the launch of Stories. Stories are a brand new type of content for social networks that allow users to quickly and easily combine photos, videos and text into beautiful multimedia vignettes and post them to their news feed alongside traditional photo or status updates.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">23snaps offers parents a private place to save photos, videos, and updates of their children, but Stories mark a departure from content types typical to other social networks, which do not offer users the ability to create a clear narrative from a series of related updates. Stories were inspired by the fact that it takes more than one photo or comment to tell the best family stories.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Meaghan Fitzgerald, Chief Marketing Officer of 23snaps says, “Over 20% of posts added to 23snaps’ contain multiple photos and 40% include detailed descriptions so we could see that families using 23snaps were interested in creating multimedia content.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"> "Stories takes that one step further by allowing parents, who are great natural storytellers, to use an unlimited combination of photos, videos and text to share a single narrative from beginning to end, tell stories about their children’s lives and share them privately with loved ones.”</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">A <a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/jenniferrooney/2012/07/17/forget-supermoms-its-all-about-the-smart-moms-survey/" target="_blank">2012 Forbes study found that nearly 40% of mothers blogged</a> in some form further indicating the desire of parents to escape the constraints placed by existing social network content formats.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Stories will be available on 23snaps’ free iPhone, iPad and Android apps, as well as on the 23snaps website. 23snaps launched in June, 2012 and recently announced they have signed on over half a million users from 179 countries.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Pete-goes-to-Mauritius_iphone_black_portrait-resized-200px.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-39740096381" alt="Pete goes to Mauritius_iphone_black_portrait (resized 200px)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Pete-goes-to-Mauritius_iphone_black_portrait-resized-200px.png" width="201" height="406" /></a><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Sarahs-First-Birthday_iphone_black_portrait-resized-200px.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-39740096383 alignleft" alt="Sarah's First Birthday_iphone_black_portrait (resized 200px)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Sarahs-First-Birthday_iphone_black_portrait-resized-200px.png" width="199" height="401" /></a></p>
<i>-- About 23snaps --</i>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><i>23snaps, <a href="http://www.23snaps.com/" target="_blank">http://www.23snaps.<wbr />com</a> is a private social network for families that allows parents to save photos, videos, updates and stories of their children, share them privately with loved ones around the world, and even order photo books and prints of their favourite snaps. </i></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><i>Founded by Ivailo Jordanov and Yury Tereshchenko in 2012, 23snaps has surpassed 500,000 users in 179 different countries and is available for free on iPhone, iPad, Android, Windows 8, online and through a wi-fi enabled, digital photo frame.</i></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><i>23snaps has been awarded a Lovie for best Lifestyle app, been selected by The Next Web Boost accelerator program and  SmartUK has shortlisted 23snaps as one of the UK’s most innovative mobile companies. </i></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-media-center/">Return to the Media Center</a></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Charlotte&#039;s Story</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740096467</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740096467</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[On March 18th, 2013 my daughter Charlotte was born. My husband Ben and I were elated and so in love, but it was a very stressful time. Due to pre eclampsia, she was delivered by C section at 31 weeks gestation. Charlotte weighed two pounds, eight ounces at birth and was 39 centimeters long. She needed respiratory aid, a central line into her belly button and an IV. She was admitted to the NICU where she spent over eight long weeks before coming home.

I first read about 23snaps in Canadian Living magazine while on bed rest in hospital. It appealed to me because Ben and I have family and friends across the globe and we would want to share regular updates of our little one once the baby arrived. I downloaded the app right away then promptly forgot about it when Charlotte arrived so suddenly.

About a week after Charlotte was born I was discharged and having to leave my fragile baby at the hospital at the end of the day was heart wrenching. It was then that I first turned to 23snaps as a way to share our sweet little one with the world she had been born into. Immediately the response we got were overwhelming, all our family felt really involved and to this day, my aunt in Scotland talks about the magic of the 23snaps app and how it helped her feel connected to us during the anxious time.

When you have a baby in critical care you are beyond exhausted and emotional. However, 23snaps was a light at the end of my long day at the hospital. I would choose a photo from the day to post and know that our loved ones were sharing in Charlotte's journey and growth. To be honest it kept a few of our relatives quiet, in the sense that they weren't calling or emailing all the time for updates because I was posted growth information and photos on 23snaps. That was a huge relief for us. We loved reading the comments posted. Often I would reread them while sitting near to Charlotte's incubator during the day and smile.

In a sense 23snaps helped me feel in control of the hospital experience. When recently looked back on the photos I picked to add to our timeline, I was surprised. I thought I had only chosen happy photos, but I realized there were some that had been taken on difficult days, such as when Charlotte had a setback and had to move from her hospital crib back into an incubator. I think being able to share the good and bad stories was therapeutic and healing for me.

Charlotte is now a healthy, happy one year old. We continue to use 23snaps, I think if we stopped there would be an outcry from our family! I know that someday, sooner than I am ready to admit, Charlotte will ask to see what I'm doing and I will show her the timeline of photos. We will look through every one and talk about how far she has come, how brave she was and how she inspires a lot of people around the world. And she will say, "wow", as she does so well, about the concept of 23snaps.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<div class="centered"><a style="color: #40689a;" href="http://app.appsflyer.com/id526481189?pid=Website&amp;c=footer" target="_blank"><img src="http://wwwsnaps.global.ssl.fastly.net/images/store-apple.png" alt="" /></a>  <a style="color: #40689a;" href="http://app.appsflyer.com/com.snaps23.android?pid=website&amp;c=footer" target="_blank"><img src="http://wwwsnaps.global.ssl.fastly.net/images/store-google.png" alt="" /></a>  <a style="color: #40689a;" href="http://apps.microsoft.com/windows/app/23snaps/8d8b50ab-fc02-49c5-a648-06b8fd586f9f" target="_blank"><img src="http://wwwsnaps.global.ssl.fastly.net/images/store-windows.png" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="centered"><em>Download the free app for iPhone, iPad, Android and Windows 8.</em></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Archive</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/archive/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2014 13:47:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lucy]]></dc:creator>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps’ Stories are changing the way people share content online</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-media-center/23snaps-stories-are-changing-the-way-people-share-content-online/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 24 Jul 2014 11:51:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lucy]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740096612</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><i>July 2014, London, UK -</i> <a href="http://www.23snaps.com">23snaps'</a> Stories, a new approach to sharing content in context, have quickly become the favored format for content consumption among their user base.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">In March 2014, the family-focused photo sharing app 23snaps announced the release of Stories. Stories enable the families on 23snaps to benefit from a more versatile method of sharing memories and experiences, and were designed to fill a gap in the way people were sharing their content online. Stories allow a complete narrative to be told from beginning to end in a way that is both simple and enjoyable - an option that is not currently offered by any of the more prominent social networks.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Since their release, Stories have become the most popular type of post for content consumers, regularly receiving a far higher number of likes and comments than photos, videos or status updates. Only 7% of the photos uploaded to 23snaps receive more than 5 comments, whilst 21% of all Stories amass this level of engagement.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Stories include an average number of photos that is 29% higher than when multiple photos are uploaded as a regular post. Content creators choose to share more photos per upload as a Story as they are able to put them in context for their friends and family. Stories have also overtaken the number of height and weight measurements uploaded to 23snaps daily, an activity that has been available since the service launched in 2012.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">23snaps founder and CEO Ivailo Jordanov says “These statistics are indicative of a new trend in online sharing, social media users want to be able to share a more contextual story with their friends and family. We believe that other social networks will also see the advantage of allowing users to share content in this manner and will soon follow suit.”</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Whilst the uptake on Stories usage has increased quickly across the board, an interesting quirk is that 23snaps’ Scandanavian users that are the biggest fans of this new way of sharing their content, with over 25% regularly creating and sharing Stories.</p>

<b><i>About 23snaps:</i></b>

<p style="text-align: justify;"><i>23snaps is a private social network for families that allows parents to save photos, videos, updates and stories of their children, share them privately with loved ones around the world, and even order photo books and prints of their favourite snaps</i><i>. It is a modern take on the traditional baby book; making use of the latest technology but simple enough for every generation to use and enjoy. </i></p>

<p style="text-align: justify;"><i>Since the service was founded by Ivailo Jordanov and Yury Tereshchenko in 2012, it has </i><i>surpassed 500,000 users in 179 different countries</i><i>. 23snaps is available for free on iPhone, iPad, Android, Windows 8, online and through a wi-fi enabled, digital photo frame.</i></p>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

				<title>23snaps launches Windows Phone App</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-media-center/23snaps-launches-windows-phone-app/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 04 Sep 2014 12:04:09 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lucy]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740096615</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><i>September 2014, London, UK: </i><a href="https://23snaps.com">23snaps</a>, the private photo sharing network for families, has just achieved another milestone on its mission to become the most accessible family photo journal app for parents. This week, the service launched their version of the app for Windows Phone, which has a whole new layout specially designed for the platform. Despite the Windows specific design, all of the distinctive features and functionalities found in the iOS and Android versions of the app that make 23snaps unique, are still included the new Windows Phone app.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Windows-Phone-1.png" alt="" width="150" />   <img src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Windows-Phone-2.png" alt="" width="150" /> <img src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Windows-Phone-3.png" alt="" width="150" /> <img src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Windows-Phone-4.png" alt="" width="150" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">According to the <a href="http://www.idc.com/getdoc.jsp?containerId=prUS25037214">latest IDC report</a>, Windows have now taken 3rd place in the global smart phone market, following Android &amp; iOS. With the inclusion of their new release, 23snaps is now able to provide a native experience to more than 98% of all smartphone users, worldwide. Ivailo Jordanov, 23snaps Founder &amp; CEO says "Having already built apps for iOS &amp; Android, the next logical step was to build for Windows Phone. Now that 23snaps has entered the Windows Phone apps market, it has become the first application of its kind to provide a fully native experience to users across all of the most popular online platforms".</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><em>About 23snaps</em></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">23snaps is an UK based private photo sharing network for families. Since its launch in June 2012, 23snaps has surpassed 500,000 users across 179 countries. The service is completely free, and is currently available on iPhone, iPad, Android, Windows 8, Windows Phone, online and through a wi-fi enabled, digital photo frame.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>About 23snaps</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/about-23snaps/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 26 Sep 2014 10:29:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lucy]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?page_id=39740096682</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="aligncenter" src="http://images.mxpnl.com/232736/1384781848894.103580.23snaps-devices.png" alt="" />
<div class="public-section">
<div class="section-inner narrow">
<h3></h3>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">WHAT IS <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23SNAPS</a>?</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23snaps</a> is a secure mobile app that allows parents to save and share photos, videos and updates of their children with a select group of family and friends.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">With families and privacy in mind, the free <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23snaps</a> app allows parents to capture their children’s precious moments as they happen in a beautiful digital journal. Updates can be shared easily and securely with close family and friends, either in real time or through beautifully presented email digests.</p>
&nbsp;

</div>
</div>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">WHERE THE IDEA CAME FROM</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Our co-founder was inspired to build <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23snaps</a> when his wife was pregnant. Like many people nowadays, our families are spread far and wide, yet we wanted them to be a part of our children’s lives, to be able to share in every special moment and milestone, however far away they might live.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">What we needed was a simple yet beautiful way to store and share photos, videos and updates, so that even our least techie family members would be able to access them easily. With a young family to think of, privacy was high on our list of priorities too; we only wanted to share our precious moments with our family and closest friends ... and so <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23snaps</a> was born.</p>
&nbsp;
<div class="public-section" style="text-align: center;">
<div class="section-inner narrow">
<h3>OUR MISSION</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Our mission with <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23snaps</a> is to make it incredibly easy to create stunning digital journals to chronicle precious memories of your child’s life, allow families to feel closer to each other as they share the experience of watching a child grow and create truly secure and private ways to share photos and videos with the people you love.
We’re incredibly proud of how <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23snaps</a> has grown already, creating smiles and bringing families from all over the world closer together. Best of all, we can use <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23snaps</a> ourselves to capture wonderful memories of our children - memories we can share with those closest to us.</p>
&nbsp;

</div>
</div>
<div class="public-section" style="text-align: center;">
<div class="section-inner narrow">
<h3>WHY <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23SNAPS</a>?</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Snaps is the casual English word for photographs, while the number 23 was inspired by the number of pairs of chromosomes that make up a human’s genetic code. Just like it takes more than one gene to make a baby, it takes more than one photograph to tell the whole story of that baby’s life. Put those ideas together, and you have <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23snaps</a>!</p>
&nbsp;

</div>
</div>
<div class="public-section">
<div class="section-inner narrow">
<h3 style="text-align: center;">DOWNLOAD <a href="”http://23snaps.com”">23SNAPS</a> NOW</h3>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://app.appsflyer.com/id526481189?pid=Website&amp;c=blog"><img src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/App-Store-button.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://app.appsflyer.com/com.snaps23.android?pid=website&amp;c=blog"><img src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Play-Store-button1.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://www.windowsphone.com/en-gb/store/app/23snaps/e5265be8-d2c2-4be1-a8c9-636e3b40af1a"><img src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Windows-Phone-Store-button.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://apps.microsoft.com/windows/app/23snaps/8d8b50ab-fc02-49c5-a648-06b8fd586f9f"><img src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Windows-Store-button.png" alt="" /></a></h2>
<div class="app-store-badges" style="text-align: center;"></div>

	<item>
				<title>Photo Sharing &amp; Storage Tools For Every Member Of The Family</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/photo-sharing-storage-tools-for-every-member-of-the-family/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 16 Dec 2014 16:00:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lucy]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740097216</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">In our increasingly digital world, sharing content online is becoming the go-to method for interacting with friends and family. The great thing about getting online is that it makes it so easy to keep up to date with far flung family members, as you can share things in real-time. However, it's not fair to assume that everyone in the family is comfortable with going digital. Sharing photos on the internet is still a relatively new concept (especially in Grandparent terms!).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Just because you can share online, doesn't necessarily mean that it's the best choice for your particular group of friends and family. Whether you decide to stick with sending physical photo prints the old fashioned way - by post, sending out digital copies by email, or setting up an online platform that allows you to post photos in a digital album, there is a tool for everyone. Don't forget, we know of one <a href="https://23snaps.com?utm_source=social&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=photo_tools">spectacular tool</a> that will enable you to edit, curate, manage AND share your photos, that will make photo sharing so much easier for multigenerational use.</p>
We've outlined some great photo sharing and storage options that will work for each family member, depending what they're comfortable with.

&nbsp;
<h5>Tools for the "I hate tech" family member</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Some people are being dragged into the new digital age kicking and screaming, but if all you want to do is share photos then there is absolutely no need to force a technophobe to get online. There are plenty services that cater to the non tech users, allowing you to order prints of your digital photos that can be posted to them simply, easily, and for a great price. It's so lovely to have a physical, tangible copy of those photos you cherish so much, and whilst you’re ordering copies to be sent out to family members, it might remind you to order a few for yourself!</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">One of the really exciting aspects of these photo printing services is that you have so many more options than just the standard 4x6” prints; as lovely as those can be. You can order beautiful photobooks, calendars, wall canvases, posters, mugs and even t-shirts … the options seem to be endless. Snapfish and Photobox are a couple of great options here.</p>
&nbsp;
<h5>Tools for the "new to tech" family member</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Take Grandma for example, she's pretty good with her computer and tablet, and has no issues accessing her email, but that's about as far as her skills go. We think that's a brilliant effort; it's great when members of the older generation get involved online as it can be pretty daunting. However, whilst Grandma might see herself as a tech guru, she’s not quite as savvy with "The Facebook" as she thinks. Using a tool such as Flikr will  allow her to easily access your online photo albums, but the simple user interface shouldn’t be too challenging, leaving that tech geek impression of herself fully intact. Flickr is a great way to store and share your photos online. It helps you organise that huge mass of photos you have and offers a way for your friends and family to enjoy them with you, regardless of whether they are just down the road, or on another continent.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Dropbox would be another great choice here, as you're able to create a huge number of albums and then choose only a specific few to share with others - whilst keeping the rest completely private. Once you’ve created the album you want to share with Grandma, she can simply login to her own Dropbox account and check out all the new photos you’ve uploaded. This is also a fantastic way to keep all of your digital photos backed up.</p>
&nbsp;
<h5>Tools for the "concerned about the security of tech" family member</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">It's understandable that when it comes to sharing photos, which are basically an uncensored view into your life, that you want to keep them private. It is definitely possible to keep photos private and secure on sites such as Flikr, Google+ and Facebook, but if you’re uncomfortable with the idea of large scale sharing and prefer the idea of a simple back and forth, you can turn to that reliable stand-by; email. Email is the classic online “sharing” platform, and there is absolutely nothing wrong with sticking with what you know.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">For the privacy conscious amongst us there is also <a href="https://23snaps.com?utm_source=social&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=photo_tools">23snaps</a>; the free private app and website. 23snaps will allow you to share your photos with a select group online. Your friends and family can choose to register their own account and join your network of connections, or subscribe to email updates from you if they’d prefer not to have to sign-up. Either way, you can share your photos safe in the knowledge that you have the ultimate control over who can access them.</p>
&nbsp;
<h5>Tools for the "confident with, but little time for, tech" family member</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">When you post photos to Google+, they are automatically curated to pull the best quality photos and put them front and centre. You then have the option of sharing these photos with individuals, a “circle” of friends and/or family, or with the public. This would be a fantastic way to share photos with someone in your family who is completely comfortable with tech, but may have limited time, or opportunity, to check your updates yet doesn’t want to miss out. Maybe they're always at work, or travel a lot? But when they do have a moment to log in, your best photos will be highlighted, making sure nothing is missed.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This is a fantastic tool for the traveller too, as any photos taken on a wifi enabled device such as a smartphone, tablet, or wifi camera will be automatically backed up whenever there is a viable wifi connection. This will prevent the loss of any photos whilst allowing friends and family back home to check in and see how the trip is going.</p>
&nbsp;
<h5>Tools for the "master of tech" family member</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Some of your family members may be so connected, you could pretty much share your photos anywhere and they would be able to find them. The mainstream social networks like Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram are the most commonly used. Instagram allows your family and friends to follow you and share in all of the photos that you post, whereas Twitter and Facebook are as equally focused on text updates as on the photos you share. These platforms allow you to share your photos easily with a large group of friends and family, although it may not be the most private way to do so. Depending on your privacy settings and the number of people in your network, you're potentially posting your photos for hundreds of people to see. Nonetheless, these are by far the most common photo sharing platforms, with over 350 million photos being uploaded to Facebook every single day.</p>
&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: justify;">Whether you’re glued to your smartphone or computer, or you’re happier leafing through a photo album, there are numerous ways to share photos with every generation, it’s just a case of finding the right ones for everyone involved.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>MUST HAVE New Year&#039;s Resolutions for Parents</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/must-have-new-years-resolutions-for-parents/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2014 12:30:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lucy]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740097243</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">Christmas is over, which means 2015 is nearly upon us! Every year we make New Year's Resolutions that we feel will improve our lifestyle, increase our fitness or change bad habits but, let's be honest, how many of us actually keep them?!</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">That's why this year we've come up with a list of resolutions that we will (hopefully) be more inclined to keep, because otherwise we might just go mad.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">If you have any other resolutions that you think might help parents to get through the next year, let us know in the comments!</p>


<p style="text-align: justify;">1. I will not buy sugary, processed treats for my children, and then end up eating them all myself after they're in bed.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">2. I will install a lock on the bathroom door to prevent "surprise" visits from my children during my alone time.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">3. I will make sure that any clothes I wear have no more than one obvious stain at any one time.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">4. I will not to buy toys that require more than 2 batteries, or make noise that can be heard more than 1 room away.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">5. I will remain straight faced when attempting to reprimand my kids for copying my less than perfect behaviour.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">6. I will not walk barefoot around the house, therefore preventing me from any crippling Lego induced injuries.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">7. I will not to eat the chewed up and discarded leftovers off my child's plate.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">8. I will not watch Frozen more than once a week.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">9. I will only cook ONE dinner, even if it's brussel sprouts - all family members WILL EAT IT and they will LIKE IT.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">10. I will attempt to keep at least ONE of the above NINE resolutions.</p>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Top 3 Things To Remember When Documenting The Holidays</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/top-3-things-to-remember-when-documenting-the-holidays/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2014 11:30:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lucy]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740097254</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">Even back in the "olden days" of analogue cameras, Christmas was one of the times of year that family photos were going to be taken, no ifs, ands, or buts. So whilst we're snap happy pretty much every day of the year now, it's still worth taking the time to consider the following points and make those Holiday photos extra special.</p>
&nbsp;
<h5>Consider Your Combinations</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">If you have a large family, it's next to impossible to wrangle everybody into one shot. Whilst it is lovely to have photo of the whole family, don't spend your time concentrating solely on that. If there are branches of the family that don't get to see each other that often, this is a great opportunity to take photos of groups that might not come together at any time of year. Have you got a photo of Great Granny cuddling the newest baby to join the brood? Have the cousins gotten together for a "begrudging teenage smile" group shot? Try and catch impromptu moments of people just spending time together - after all, it only comes but once a year.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grandparents-and-baby.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-39740097269 size-medium" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grandparents-and-baby-300x207.png" alt="23snaps - Documenting The Holidays" width="300" height="207" /></a></p>
&nbsp;
<h5>Hand Over Control</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">You are probably up to your eyeballs organising gifts to exchange, cooking dinner and making sure the kids don't eat themselves into a sugar coma - so let someone else (or multiple someones) take some of the photos. You could even grab a whole load of cheap disposable cameras and lets the kids join in as mini photographers for the day.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/kid-with-camera.jpeg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-39740097270" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/kid-with-camera.jpeg" alt="23snaps - Documenting The Holidays" width="300" height="200" /></a></p>
&nbsp;
<h5>Remember To Include Yourself in the Photos!</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We're all so used to capturing the cute things that our little ones do, that we often forget to get photos with ourselves in them too. If you can think of 3 photos of yourself, with the kids (that you actually like!), that have been taken in the last few months - we'd be impressed. Step out from behind the camera and capture the memories of <em>you</em> enjoying Christmas with your families. You'll regret it if you don't!</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-39740097271 size-medium" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/mom-and-baby-300x255.jpg" alt="23snaps - Documenting The Holidays" width="300" height="255" /></p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Happy New Year From 23snaps</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/happy-new-year-from-23snaps/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 2015 12:01:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lucy]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740097281</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[HAPPY 2015 EVERYONE!!
<p style="text-align: justify;">Another year begins, and we're all poised to get to work keeping our New Year's resolutions (at least for a week or 2!). Time seems to speed by so fast, don't forget to document all of the special moments you make with your family, and save them all on your dedicated <a href="https://23snaps.com?utm_source=social&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=NYE">23snaps</a> timeline.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We thought, to help you mix things up a bit, we'd share with you how different countries around the world celebrate New Years. Maybe you'll get some ideas and try something new this year?</p>
&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Australia.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097285" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Australia.png" alt="Australia" width="200" height="100" /></a>
<h5>Australia</h5>
Date Celebrated: January 1st
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Eve Traditions: Parties that begin on 31st Dec to ring in the New Year with cheers, whistles, rattles and car horns.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years DayTraditions: Outdoor activities such as rodeos, picnic races and surf carnivals.</p>
&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Brazil.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097286" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Brazil-300x210.png" alt="Brazil" width="200" height="140" /></a>
<h5>Brazil</h5>
Date Celebrated:  1st January
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Eve Traditions: Wear white clothes to signify a fresh start, and take flowers as offers to the water goddess, Yemanja, which are thrown into the sea.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Day Traditions: Serve and eat lentil soup or lentils and rice, as lentils signify wealth. This is to encourage prosperousness in the coming year.</p>
&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/China.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097287" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/China-300x199.png" alt="China" width="200" height="133" /></a>
<h5>China</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Date Celebrated: Between January 21 and February 20 (exact date is fixed by the lunar calendar)</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years DayTraditions: The Chinese New Year "<i>Yuan Tan</i>" is a time for feasting, visiting relatives and friends, but in the city a spectacular procession takes place. The celebrations are based on bringing luck, health, happiness, and wealth till the next year. They clean their houses to rid them of lasts year's bad luck before the celebrations begin.</p>
&nbsp;
<h5><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/England.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097288" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/England.png" alt="England" width="200" height="120" /></a></h5>
<h5>England</h5>
Date Celebrated: January 1st
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Eve Traditions: Crowds of people gather inLondon to hear the chimes of London's Big Ben announces the arrival of the New Year, and watch the spectacular firework display. Groups stands around with arms linked to sing Auld Lang Syne.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Day Traditions: New Year's Day is a National holiday, most people stay at home and spend time with their families.</p>
&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Greece.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097289" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Greece-300x199.png" alt="Greece" width="200" height="133" /></a>
<h5>Greece</h5>
Date Celebrated: January 1st
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Eve Traditions: Greek housewives hang the pomegranate on or above their doors throughout the 12 days of Christmas. Right before midnight comes on New Year’s Eve, all family members get out of the house and the lights are shut down to let go of the old year. When the New Year begins at 12am, the fruit is smashed against the door of the house as a sign of welcoming the New Year and breaking loose its positive prospects. The more seeds scattered on the floor, the luckier the year will be.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Day Traditions: On New Year's Day, the most important dish is  served. The Vassilopitta is a cake dedicated to St Basil, and inside the cake is placed a silver or gold coin. Whoever finds the coin in their piece of cake will be lucky for the next year.</p>
&nbsp;
<h5><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/netherlands.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097290" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/netherlands-300x195.jpg" alt="netherlands" width="200" height="130" /></a></h5>
<h5>Netherlands</h5>
Date Celebrated: January 1st
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Eve Traditions: In the Netherlands people burn Christmas trees on street bonfires and let off fireworks to ring in the New Year and as a way of driving out the spirits of the old year.</p>
&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/South-Afirca.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097291" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/South-Afirca-300x199.png" alt="South Afirca" width="200" height="133" /></a>
<h5>South Africa</h5>
Date Celebrated: January 1st
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Eve Traditions: In South Africa they ring in the New Year with church bells ringing and gunshots being fired.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Day Traditions: New Year's Day is full of a carnival atmosphere as there are carnivals where people dress in colourful costumes and dance in streets to the sound of drums.</p>
&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/thailand.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097292" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/thailand-300x199.png" alt="Thailand" width="200" height="133" /></a>
<h5>Thailand</h5>
Date Celebrated: April 13th to 15th
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Day Traditions: The New Year celebrations start by people chasing each other down the street with buckets of water, as they believe it will bring good rains in the coming year. People then visit the monastery to pray and offer gifts of rice, fruit, sweets and other foods for the monks.</p>
&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/US-upside-down-e1417190542681.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097293" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/US-upside-down-e1417190542681-300x157.jpg" alt="US (upside down)" width="200" height="105" /></a>
<h5>United States</h5>
Date Celebrated: January 1st
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Eve Traditions: People gather in Times Square (New York City) to watch the ball drop hosted by Dick Clark. This is broadcast all over the United States, so those not in New York can watch the festivities on TV. Like in England, at midnight people link arms and sing Auld Lang Syne, people also kiss to prevent a year of loneliness.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">New Years Day Traditions: The first day of the New Year is the traditional date for many post-season college football bowl games, which are usually accompanied by parades and other activities to celebrate the events.</p>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

		<wp:ping_status>closed</wp:ping_status>
