	<item>
				<title>5 Cool Things You Can Do on 23snaps </title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/5-cool-things-you-can-do-on-23snaps/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 04 Jan 2015 12:00:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rachell]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740097297</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">We all know that 23snaps helps you to save and privately share your children's special moments with your loved ones, right?</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">But with a fresh new year just getting started, we thought it would be a good idea <strong>to show you a few cool things about 23snaps</strong> that you might not know yet in order to help you to get the most of the service.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Here are the 5 cool features available on 23snaps that you (maybe) didn't know about until now:</p>

<a href="”http://pinterest.com”" target="”_blank”">1- Order books and prints straight from your Collections (iOS and website):</a>
<h5>1- Order books and prints straight from your Collections (iOS and website):</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">If you like to upload your photos and separate them into Collections, then you will love this feature! Create a beautiful printed album from your specially curated a Collections, to allow you to enjoy all of the extra special moments, without needing an internet connection! To order a selection of prints or a full photobook from your favourite Collections, simply follow the instructions below:</p>

<em>- On iOS:</em>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Tap the 'More' button and select 'Collections'. Then simply open the Collection you would like to print and click on the <em>Polaroid Photo</em> icon next to the Collection title. Choose whether you want to place a book or prints order, then you'll be shown the photos that will be included. If you'd like to add more photos to it, simply tap the "Add More Photos" button, to select more images or hit "Back" to add another entire Collection (then you just have to repeat the original process with your next Collection).</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">If you're ordering a photobook, once you've made your selection, you'll have the option to preview the finished product and page through your book. If you're not satisfied with the order, simply hit Back and make your edits. When you are ready, hit the 'Preview' button again and then proceed to the checkout page.</p>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4192.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097308" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4192.png" alt="IMG_4192" width="160" /></a>  <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4189.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097305" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4189.png" alt="IMG_4189" width="160" /></a>  <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4190.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097306" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4190.png" alt="IMG_4190" width="160" /></a>  <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4191.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097307" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4191.png" alt="IMG_4191" width="160" /></a>

<em>- On the website:</em>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Click on the 'My Family' tab from the menu bar and then click on the 'Collections' button on the right of your family profile. Then select one of your Collections. Once opened you will see the option to either 'Order Book' or 'Order Prints'. After choosing your prefered option you will have the chance to preview your selection of photos and to add more photos to it if you'd like.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.30.34-with-arrow.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097313" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.30.34-with-arrow.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.30.34 with arrow" width="230" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.33.54.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097310" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.31.23.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.31.23" width="230" /></a><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.33.54.png"> </a><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.33.54.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-39740097311 alignnone" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.33.54.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.33.54" width="230" /></a></p>
<em> </em>
<h5>2- The Time Machine (iOS and Android only)</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Time Machine is a great tool to help remind you of some of the best moments you and your family have shared in the past, with a randomly generated selection of old and new photos that you've uploaded to 23snaps. You will be surprised to see how fast your little ones change and grow over such a short period of time!</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Before using this feature, you need to make sure you've uploaded a good amount of photos to your 23snaps account. You can then access the Time Machine from the 'More' menu button, if you are on iOS, or by tapping the top left Menu button, if you're on Android. Once you've opened the Time Machine page, every time you shake your phone you will see a different selection of photos with the dates they were taken clearly displayed. If we do say so ourselves, we think this is a pretty cool tool ... you'll really feel like you're time travelling!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_41921.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097316" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_41921.png" alt="IMG_4192" width="185" /></a>  <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4193.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097317" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4193.png" alt="IMG_4193" width="185" /></a>  <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4195.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097318" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4195.png" alt="IMG_4195" width="185" /></a></p>
<em> </em>
<h5>3- Connect your Instagram account to 23snaps (website only):</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Did you know you can have all of your Instagram photos posted automatically on 23snaps as well? All you need to do is to add the tag #23snaps to your Instagram posts. This is a really handy feature if you like to use other social media channels to share photos of your family!</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">In order to integrate the 2 accounts, simply go to the <a href=" https://www.23snaps.com/account/social%20">Social Settings</a> page in your 23snaps account, open the Instagram tab and click on the "Connect" button. You will then be required to enter your Instagram account login details to complete the connection process.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.37.52-with-arrow.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097320" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.37.52-with-arrow.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.37.52 with arrow" width="235" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.38.13.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097321" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.38.13.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.38.13" width="210" /></a>
<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/instagram-to-23snaps-1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097332" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/instagram-to-23snaps.png" alt="instagram to 23snaps" width="160" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097331" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/instagram-to-23snaps-1.png" alt="instagram to 23snaps 1" width="160" /></a></p>
&nbsp;

<em> </em>
<h5>4- Tagging your friends' kids (iOS, Android and website)</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Having the option to tag your connections' children in your photos was one of the most requested features of 2014. We were very happy when we were finally able to release this feature it at the end of the year! Now, when your kids spend the weekend with the Grandparents; Grandma or Grandpa can share those photos from their own 23snaps account and still add them directly to your children's timelines, simply by tagging them. You can also add photos of your nieces and nephew to their own timelines, whenever it's your turn to have all of the kids.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Since your privacy is our number one priority, whenever anyone in your network wants to tag one of your little ones, you will receive a notification that gives you the opportunity to accept or decline the tag.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">To tag the children in your network simply:</p>

<em>- On iOS and Android:</em>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Follow the normal upload process to share the photos of your connections' children. Then click on the 'Tag your friends' children' option located below each picture on the publishing page and select which children you would like to tag. Once you've made any desired edits and added your descriptions, simply hit the 'Finish' button.</p>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4187-with-arrow.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097329" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4187-with-arrow.png" alt="IMG_4187 with arrow" width="185" /></a>

<em>- On the website:</em>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Again, follow the normal upload process to share the photos of your connections' children. Then click on the 'Other Children' option located next to each picture in the publishing page, and then hit the 'Publish' button.</p>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.15.40-with-arrow.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097322" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.15.40-with-arrow.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.15.40 with arrow" width="400" /></a>

<em> </em>
<h5>5- Nudge your family and friends (website, iOS and Android)</h5>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Are you connected to a friend or family member who doesn't post very often and you are missing the enjoyment of seeing their new photos? Why not send them a little 'Nudge' to remind them that you want to see more of their family updates? You can do so from either the website or from the app:</p>

<em>- On the website:</em>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Go to your <a href="https://www.23snaps.com/me/connections">Family &amp; Friends</a> page and select the profile of the family you're missing. On their family page, click on the 'Nudge' button located at the top right corner and add a little personalised message. Then just click the orange 'Send Nudge' button to complete the process.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.44.40.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097336 size-medium" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.44.40-300x269.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.44.40" width="300" height="269" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.45.20-with-arrow.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097337" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.45.20-with-arrow-300x272.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.45.20 with arrow" width="296" height="269" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.45.46.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-39740097338" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screen-Shot-2014-12-12-at-10.45.46-300x279.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-12-12 at 10.45.46" width="289" height="269" /></a></p>
<em>- On iOS and Android:</em>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Open the 'My Friends' option from the 'More' menu (on iOS) or the left hand Menu button (on Android). Then select the profile of the family you want to nudge. Please note that on the app the Nudge button is only available for families who have added a child profile to their page. If this is the case for your connection, simply click on their child's profile photo and then click on the 'Nudge' button in the top right corner of the page.  Then, add a little personalised message and hit 'Send' to let them know you miss them.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4197.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097340" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4197.png" alt="IMG_4197" width="185" /></a>  <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/nudge-with-arrow.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097342" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/nudge-with-arrow.png" alt="nudge with arrow" width="185" />  <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740097341" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_4200.png" alt="IMG_4200" width="185" /></a></p>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Why are we building 23snaps?</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/26247265252/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 01 Jul 2012 02:02:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/26247265252</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p align="center"><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m6i8wj1AHG1rqaa0a.png" alt=""/>
<p>A lot of people ask us how the idea of 23snaps came about and what makes us passionate about it?</p>
<p>The idea of 23snaps started to form on the 30th of December 2011. At the time, my wife and I were expecting our first child and while talking to my parents, they jokingly said that once the little one is born, either we send them lots of photos and videos or they will move in with us to be close to him. As much as I love my parents, the size of our apartment makes the latter impossible, so I began looking for ways to keep them virtually connected to their grandson. </p>
<p>Simply put, I wanted a private social network that would keep us connected with our family and close friends, would be easy for our parents to use and, most importantly, it would enable my wife and I to manage our son&#8217;s entries together. I am an active Facebook/Instagram/Path/&lt;insert service here&gt; user, and have been since the early days of all of them, but I didn&#8217;t feel that any of the existing sites offered what I was looking for. That&#8217;s how 23snaps began. The first line of code was written at the end of January 2012 and the first version of the app was available on the App store at the end of May. </p>
<p>It has now been a month since our first public debut and while we are still in very early stages of our product development, it has been amazing to see how 23snaps is bringing families from all over the world closer. Currently 23snaps connects people from 74 countries with their families every day. The content is so precious that when someone posts something, nearly everyone that they are connected with logs in to look at the post and we know that it brings a smile to their face.</p>
<p>There is no virtual substitute for real life interactions and 23snaps is not trying to be one, but with our busy lives and constant moving around, we&#8217;d like to believe that 23snaps is providing an enhancement, a way to stay close even when you are far apart and that is what makes us passionate about what we are creating.</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Meet the 23snaps team</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/26663285940/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 07 Jul 2012 00:29:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/26663285940</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We&#8217;re excited to introduce you to the 23snaps team. </p>
<p align="center"><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m6rknkOGt71rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/>
<p>All of the inspiration for 23snaps comes from our children. It is because we want to capture every magic moment, share it with the people we love and make them smile that we are building the application. The best part about working on the project is that we get to experience it every day. It&#8217;s amazing and inspiring to see our kids timelines grow full of new memories, which we can treasure forever.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/27206147882/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 14 Jul 2012 18:45:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/27206147882</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p align="center"><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m75yrcklP91rqaa0a.png" alt=""/>
<p>We are excited to announce that there is an update waiting for you to <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/23snaps/id526481189?ls=1&amp;mt=8" target="_blank">download from the App store</a>. It brings you some photo management functionality like filters and vignettes to apply to your photos, as well as the ability to crop and adjust them to be square.</p>
<p>To get to the filters, once you have taken or chosen a photo from your library, tap the &#8216;Filters&#8217; button located under the photo in the add entry screen.</p>
<p>As always, let us know what you think and how can we make it better.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/31365567702/</link>

				<title>Tap magazine</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/31526963686/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 14 Sep 2012 16:24:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>

<p align="center"><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_maclivsuL41rqaa0a.png" alt=""/>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>28 Rules for fathers and sons</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/31887012937/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 19 Sep 2012 23:25:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/31887012937</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>My wife sent me a link to this post and as I was reading it I thought that all fathers of boys should read it. Even though most &#8216;rules&#8217; sound like common sense, we don&#8217;t often think about the little things. I still remember the first time my dad let me &#8220;drive&#8221; on his lap, it was the most awesome experience.</p>
<p>If you are a father of a boy, head over to Dan Pearce&#8217;s blog and have a look at <a href="http://www.danoah.com/2012/08/28-rules-for-fathers-of-sons.html" target="_blank">28 rules for fathers of sons</a>.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Upload and Import Photos to 23snaps Online</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/34295029532/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 25 Oct 2012 13:38:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/34295029532</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><p class="MsoNormal">We’ve loved hearing about how you use <a href="http://www.23snaps.com">23snaps</a> to capture memories on the go, but a lot of you have asked for the ability to upload photos from your camera, import photos from other sites, or just add a whole lot of photos all at once to your 23snaps account.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Well we hear you loud and clear so as of today, we’ve made it possible for you to add photos via the website. Simply <a href="http://23snaps.com/account/login">log in to your 23snaps</a> account and click the new ‘Add Photos’ button that appears above your news feed.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mcfzt7yQT81rqaa0a.png" alt=""/>
<p class="MsoNormal">The uploader can help you take photos from your computer, Facebook, Instagram, Picasa and Flickr and add them to 23snaps all at once. Uploading a lot of photos? Don’t worry – we’ll only notify your friends and family once about your new content, even if they have signed up to receive a notification for every update.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mcfztk48WI1rqaa0a.png" alt=""/>
<p class="MsoNormal">Best of all, you can now use 23snaps even if you don’t have an iPhone or iPad. Simply upload your photos online and your family and friends who do have Apple products can still get notifications and view your child’s photos from their phone.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">23snaps is all about sharing the love with your closest family and friends, and technology should never be a barrier. That’s why we’re making it easier for everyone to add and see those precious moments.</p></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Introducing Collections</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/34629105543/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 30 Oct 2012 09:49:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/34629105543</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><p class="MsoNormal">We hope you’re using 23snaps to capture memories every single day. But if you’re anything like us, it’s easy to snap so many pictures of your little one that favorite photos get lost in the mix.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">That’s why we’re introducing Collections, a brand new way to organize and treasure your photos. Collections are like photo albums where you can save related photos, videos and status updates – with just a few unique features that make them much better than your average album!</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mcg39uO4u41rqaa0a.png" width="275px" alt=""/><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mcg3aicelB1rqaa0a.png" width="275px" alt=""/></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Create custom collections for all of your content</strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Create your own inspired collections for Firsts, Favorites, Best Smiles, Holidays, and any other topic that helps you rediscover your favorite 23snaps content. Add photos, videos, measurements and status updates to tell the full story.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Add photos and videos to multiple collections</strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">You don’t have to pick and choose where your pictures belong – add your content to multiple collections so it’s always in the right place.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Share collections with anyone</strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Best of all, you can share collections with anyone – even people you’re not connected to and people who don’t use 23snaps. Simply open up your Collection in the mobile app and choose to Share via e-mail – and we’ll send them a sample of the photos and a unique link to access the rest of the collection online. If you haven’t authorized them to follow photos of your child, they won’t be able to see any of your other pictures or videos.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">We&#8217;d love to hear your feedback - let us know how you are using collections to organize and capture even more of the precious moments in your child&#8217;s life.</p></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Meet Babyhuddle</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/35273556400/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Nov 2012 15:46:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/35273556400</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal"><em>About this post: They say that the best ideas online are born out of personal need. We started 23snaps based on our own desire to have a private place to share special moments with our loved ones. We asked our friend Walid Al Saqqaf, the founder of Babyhuddle, to tell us the story of why he decided to create his website.</em></p>
<hr><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_md2mgiTeN41rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/>
<p class="MsoNormal">Just over 2.5 years ago, my wife and I found out we were pregnant (!) with our first child. It was such a thrilling time. We got excited at all the things we would do and get for her when she finally entered the world.  After browsing several online shop it wasn’t long before we felt utterly overwhelmed and confused. Too much information was scattered around in a seemingly random way.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">What was a swaddle? How would we use it? Was it necessary / the best option? Is it needed straight from birth? In our simplified world we knew we needed the basics such as a pram, cot bed, nursery furniture…etc…. but did we need a moses basket as well? What kind of nappy rash cream would be the best? Are grobags comfortable for her to sleep in? What monitor would be the safest?</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">We could go on and on listing all the questions we had and subsequently, a fear of potentially not being prepared for the birth of our child developed. In the end, we found that the tips other parents had on what products were best to get, when to use them, and how to use them provided us with much thought out answers. Another stumbling block we came across was having to visit so many stores in order to find all the products we wanted. ‘If only there was a one stop shop for all of the best products and advice!’ we kept repeating to each other.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">It is at this moment we felt that there should be a better way to do all of this. One that involved less stress, more fun, and a feeling of being part of a community of parents who shared top tips and encouraged each other. From this, <a href="http://babyhuddle.com/" title="Babyhuddle" target="_blank"><span>Babyhuddle</span></a> was born.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">We launched <a href="http://babyhuddle.com/">Babyhuddle</a> in the UK in November 2011 as a social site for parents to share top tips by creating lists of baby products on any topics such as <a href="http://babyhuddle.com/travelling/list/things-for-short-and-long-car-trip/">Things for Short and Long Car Trip</a>, <a href="http://babyhuddle.com/playtime-stimulation/list/toddler-swimming-essentials/">Toddler Swimming Essentials</a> and <a href="http://babyhuddle.com/books/list/favourite-family-books/">Favourite Family Books</a> to name a few. Parents can also write product reviews to asking &amp; answering questions on any topics such as <a href="http://babyhuddle.com/nappies-potty/ask/how-did-you-start-potty-training/">How did you start potty training?</a> and <span><a href="http://babyhuddle.com/feeding/ask/introducing-baby-to-savoury-tastes/">Introducing baby to savoury tastes?</a></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">We’ve also just launched in the US and can be found on <a href="http://us.babyhuddle.com/">us.babyhuddle.com</a>.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">We’d love to have you join us on <a href="https://babyhuddle.com/account/signup/">Babyhuddle UK</a> or <a href="https://us.babyhuddle.com/account/signup/">Babyhuddle US</a> so that you can share your recommendations, experiences and top tips with other parents. As you know being a first time parent isn’t easy and your recommendations could really make the difference to other parents’ lives. You’ll also find that our growing community of like minded parents are always happy to help answer your questions that you might have.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">We hope to see you soon on Babyhuddle.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<wp:post_id>36215448509</wp:post_id>

	<item>
				<title>Types of Content Updates in 23snaps</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/36349097674/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Nov 2012 20:12:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/36349097674</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>23snaps is about so much more than simply photo sharing! With 23snaps you can not only add photos, but record videos, add text updates, and record height and weight measurements of your children to tell the whole story.</p>
<p>Learn more about the different type of content updates you add in 23snaps.</p>
<img align="left" alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mdxw0m3UKG1rqaa0a.png" width="200" alt=""/>
<p><strong>Getting Started</strong></p>
<p>While you can always <a href="http://23snaps.com/Feed">upload or import photos</a> directly from your computer on the 23snaps website, to add video, status or measurement updates, for now you&#8217;ll need the <a href="http://app.appsflyer.com/id526481189?pid=Website&amp;c=blog">free 23snaps app</a>.</p>
<p>Open the app and tap the orange &#8216;Add&#8217; button to select which type of update you&#8217;d like to add, and you&#8217;ll see instructions to help you with the rest of the process.</p>
<p><br/><br/><br/><br/></p>
<p><strong><img align="left" alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mdxwa6BrJI1rqaa0a.png" width="200" alt=""/></strong></p>
<p><strong><br/></strong></p>
<p><strong>Videos</strong></p>
<p>When you select the &#8216;Video&#8217; option when adding content to 23snaps, you can either upload a video that&#8217;s already on your phone, or record a new one. </p>
<p>In both cases, you can review the video, and even choose a start and end point to make sure you&#8217;ve got the perfect recording for your child&#8217;s timeline. Videos currently have a 30 second time limit.</p>

<p><strong><br/></strong></p>
<p><strong><br/></strong></p>
<p><strong><br/></strong></p>
<p><strong>Status </strong><strong>Updates</strong></p>
<img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mdxwna9jzM1rqaa0a.png" alt=""/>
<p>Sometimes you might have some special news to share that doesn&#8217;t include a photo or video. In those cases, why not add a status update? Your updates will be included in your child&#8217;s timeline alongside pictures and videos to tell the whole story of your little one.</p>
<p><strong>Height and Weight Measurements</strong></p>
<img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mdxwiwAcxH1rqaa0a.png" width="200" alt=""/>
<p>Finally, you can keep track of your children&#8217;s growth with height and weight measurements. Just like 23snaps lets you see your child&#8217;s age when you scroll back through old pictures, these measurements can help you remember what your child was like at each precious moment.</p>
<p>Ready to get started adding your own updates? Log in or register with the free app!</p>
<p><a href="http://23snaps.com/home/apps"><img alt="image" height="40" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mekc27kf9w1rqaa0a.png" alt=""/></a> <a href="http://app.appsflyer.com/id526481189?pid=blog&amp;c=upload-types"><img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mekc2a4XBW1rqaa0a.png" alt=""/></a></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Itsy Bitsy Royal</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37182320565/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 04 Dec 2012 11:48:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37182320565</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>So Britain has a baby royal on the way!! Congratulations to Will and Kate on the announcement of their pregnancy. Preparations are bound to be underway for the arrival of His or Her (baby) Royal Highness and we’re sure the privacy of the “parents to be” will be at the top of the list of priorities. Kate has already had some issues with the press this year and so ensuring their pregnancy, and their future offspring, is kept out of the public eye will take some work. We’ve got some suggestion as to how to protect their privacy that would be useful to any parent.<br/><br/><strong><em><img align="left" height="220" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mei8mwDmE71rqaa0a.jpg" width="220" alt=""/></em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em><br/></em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em>Sunglasses to protect their privacy</em></strong></p>
<p>Maybe they should purchase some Baby BanZ? These adorable little sunglasses designed for babies, with a strap that runs right around the infant’s head to keep them snuggly in place, would be a great way to keep the paparazzi from taking unwanted snaps of the baby.</p>
<p><em><strong><br/></strong></em></p>

<p><em><strong>Watermark official photos</strong></em></p>
<p>However we’re sure that Kate and Will won’t keep all the pictures to themselves, but it would be a good idea for them to watermark any official photos they release of their new family. That way they can ensure no unauthorised copies are being used to promote products they didn’t agree to, it will help keep the image of their child protected.</p>
<p><em><strong><br/></strong></em></p>
<p><em><strong>Switch off GPS Tracking</strong></em></p>
<img align="right" height="100" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mei8g7wVyB1rqaa0a.jpg" width="200" alt=""/>When taking any photos, especially those snapped with a smartphone, we&#8217;d advise the couple turn off the GPS built in to the phones as it tags the exact location the photo was taken as it is saved. In order to prevent anyone finding out their location without their express permission, stopping the GPS from tracking the location in which a photo was taken can really help a parent ensure their privacy.</p>
<div>

<p><em><strong>Using 23snaps</strong></em></p>
<img align="left" height="190" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mei87wyhmE1rqaa0a.jpg" width="140" alt=""/>
<p>Despite trying to avoid inviting unwanted attention, we’re certain the Royal Couple will want to share certain photos of their new addition when he or she arrives and what better way to keep those photos private than by using a photo sharing platform like 23snaps, the mobile app that allows parents to save and share photos, videos and updates of their children with a select group of family and friends. There will be no need for them to worry about unwittingly broadcasting pics of their offspring to just anyone when they can use this safe, secure app to document their baby’s early years.</p>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Fun and Simple Activities for Children</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37255141664/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 05 Dec 2012 11:23:02 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37255141664</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Looking for easy and creative activities for children? We’ve got some fantastic ideas to entertain kids that don’t depend on a good weather forecast!<br/><br/>With Christmas fast approaching, we’re sure these holiday games and christmas crafts will be sure to entertain for hours on end.<br/><strong id="internal-source-marker_0.880614067427814"><br/><em>Paper Plate Angels</em></strong></p>
<img align="left" alt="image" height="250" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mek1byhSfH1rqaa0a.jpg" width="200" alt=""/>
<p>All kids will love this as they get to see their handiwork displayed beautifully on the top of your tree.</p>

<p>All you’ll need is:</p>
<ul><li>a paper plate</li>
<li>pencil</li>
<li>scissors</li>
<li>tape</li>
<li>crayons, paint, and/or glitter for decoration</li>
</ul><p>1. Draw a pattern for your angel on the underside of your paper plate<br/><img align="left" alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mek14kYqzs1rqaa0a.gif" alt=""/>
<p>2. Cut along the lines, and get rid of the excess (the top section)</p>
<p>3. Decorate your angel in any way you like</p>
<p>4. Overlap the back of your angels skirt slightly and tape into place</p>
<p>VOILA! A beautiful homemade angel.</p>
<p><br/><br/><em><strong>Keepsake Hand and Foot Prints:</strong></em></p>
<img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mek1jchSHo1rqaa0a.png" alt=""/>
<p>A great chance for kids to have fun getting messy whilst creating a memorable keepsake for you to treasure.</p>
<p>All you’ll need is:</p>
<ul><li>popsicle sticks</li>
<li>glue</li>
<li>paper</li>
<li>washable paint</li>
<li>a bucket, washing up bowl OR large dish</li>
<li>paintbrush (optional)</li>
</ul><p><br/>1. Pour a thin layer of paint into your container of choice and lay your paper on the ground</p>
<p>2. Have your little one pop their hands and feet (one at a time!), or you can brush the paint<img align="right" alt="image" height="200" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mek1kvOLli1rqaa0a.jpg" width="250" alt=""/>on directly, and then press them against the paper to leave a hand/foot print</p>
<p>3. Put the paper aside to dry and get those hands and feet washed</p>
<p>4. Glue at least 4 of the popsicle sticks together at a right angle to create a frame which can be decorated however you like</p>
<p>5. Glue to frame over the now dried hand and foot prints and cut away any excess paper.</p>
<p>These would make adorable little gifts for family members who may not get to see your kids as often as they’d like.</p>


<p><br/><em><strong>Candy Checkers:</strong></em></p>
<p>As a large part of this game includes allowing the players<img align="right" alt="image" height="200" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mek1n5mVLY1rqaa0a.jpg" width="200" alt=""/>to eat their candy, it might not be a game that is suitable for everyday, but when you do play … all the family will love it!<br/><img align="left" alt="image" height="100" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mek1r1ub971rqaa0a.jpg" width="100" alt=""/>All you’ll need is:</p>
<ul><li>a large square piece of card</li>
<li>a marker pen</li>
<li>a ruler</li>
<li>2 types of candy or cookie</li>
</ul><p><br/>1. Start by making the board, using the ruler and the marker draw a grid onto the table creating a board roughly 8x8 squares (the squares don’t have to be perfectly symmetrical but they do have to be equal along each side)</p>
<p>2. Colour in every other square to create a checkerboard effect</p>
<p>3. Take your candy and set it up like you would a normal checkers game</p>
<p>4. Every time someone takes on of the opposing players pieces … THEY GET TO EAT IT!!</p>
<p>Yum yum yum …..<br/><br/><br/>These games and crafts can provide hours of fun for your children and they can be repeated over and over again! Have fun!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Healthy Snacks</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37328365793/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 06 Dec 2012 12:23:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37328365793</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We all want to feed our kids healthy snacks. Here are some easy snacks that are quick to make that your kids will love.<br/><br/></p>
<p><em><strong>Ants on a Log</strong><img align="left" alt="image" height="200" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mekiujWobP1rqaa0a.jpg" width="200" alt=""/></em></p>
<p><em><br/></em>Made with:</p>
<ul><li>Celery</li>
<li>Raisins</li>
<li>Peanut butter (substitute for cream cheese due to allergies or personal preference)</li>
</ul><p><br/>Simply fill the hollow middle of the celery stick with the peanut butter and place the raisins along the top!<br/><br/><br/></p>
<p><em><strong>Smiley Face Crackers:<img align="left" height="200" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_melzooUtGG1rqaa0a.jpg" width="250" alt=""/></strong></em><br/><br/>Made with:</p>
<ul><li>Circular crackers</li>
<li>Green or yellow peppers</li>
<li>Cherry tomatoes or olives</li>
<li>Cucumber</li>
<li>Cream cheese</li>
</ul><p><br/>Slice the peppers into half moons, slice the cucmber and half the cherry tomatoes. Spread a thin layer of cream cheese onto the cracker so the veg will stick. Use pieces of pepper for a mouth, cherry tomato halves make eyes, and pop on a cucumber nose and you have a tasty snack that’s healthy and happy.<br/><br/></p>
<p><br/><em><strong>Rainbow Kebabs:<img align="left" alt="image" height="200" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mekiyaBI4N1rqaa0a.jpg" width="250" alt=""/></strong></em><br/><br/>Made with:</p>
<ul><li>Cheese (medium hard cheese works best like cheddar or red leicester)</li>
<li>Apple</li>
<li>Strawberries</li>
<li>Melon</li>
<li>Blueberries</li>
<li>You will also need shaped cutters (stars/hearts/circles) and wooden skewers</li>
</ul><p><br/>Slice all of your cheese, melon and apple into 1cm thick slices (a bigger cross section of the fruit will give you more space to cut your shapes). Using your cutters, create shapes with all of your ingredients. Push your ingredients onto your wooden skewers, alternating the fruits and cheese so different colours are placed next to each other to give the pretty rainbow effect.</p>
<p><br/><br/><em><strong>2 Minute Banana Ice Cream</strong></em><img align="left" alt="image" height="150" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mekizhwiUU1rqaa0a.jpg" width="250" alt=""/><br/><br/>Made with:</p>
<ul><li>Bananas (frozen)</li>
<li>Vanilla Extract</li>
<li>Whole Milk</li>
<li>You will also need a food processor</li>
</ul><p><br/>This recipe does require a little pre-planning, but that only involves remembering to pop your bananas in the freezer! The riper the banana the sweeter your ice cream will be but you can always add a little sugar to taste if you find yours isn’t living up to the dessert expectations. All you need to do is roughly slice up your frozen bananas (just to make life a little easier for your food processor), slosh in a little milk and a teaspoon of vanilla and blitz away. The blades may resist at first, but persevere and after 1-2 minutes you will have a lovely light ice cream with little more fat than a banana!!<strong id="internal-source-marker_0.3228045890573412"><br/></strong></p>]]></content:encoded>

				<title>The Golden Cowpat - the Perfect Holiday Show for Families in London</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/39041978844/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 15 Nov 2012 20:12:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/39041978844</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mdkyi61q5O1rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/>
<div>
<p>Are you and your family based in or near London, UK? Then be sure to check out <a href="http://pages.23snaps.com/win-tickets-to-the-golden-cowpat-london/">The Golden Cowpat</a> on this holiday season at the Pleasance Theatre in London!</p>
<p>One day Hector the farmer discovers a mysterious golden cowpat in his field. This sets him and Betty, his naughty cow, on a quest to sell them and make a fortune!</p>
<p>This charming family show, suitable for all ages, has received rave reviews up and down the country and is, for the first time this holiday season, coming to North London. Don&#8217;t miss your chance to share this funny, music-filled show with your little ones!</p>
<p><strong><a href="http://pages.23snaps.com/win-tickets-to-the-golden-cowpat-london/">Get your tickets now</a> and stay tuned for your chance to win tickets to this lovely show from 23snaps and The Pleasance Theatre!</strong></p>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps is Now Available on Android Phones</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37402121022/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 07 Dec 2012 13:53:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37402121022</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><p class="MsoNormal"><img align="left" alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_melr1vTRh21rqaa0a.jpg" width="175" alt=""/>We are thrilled to announce the launch of the 23snaps app for Android.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Starting today, your family and close friends who use Android phones can download the 23snaps app, get real-time updates when you add new photos or videos of your children, and start building a living memory book of their own children’s precious moments. </p>
<p class="MsoNormal">We believe that technology shouldn’t be a barrier to sharing special memories with loved ones. Now, with 23snaps available online, through email, on the iPhone and iPad, and on Android devices, we’re helping even more families stay connected to the little ones they love. The new Android version of the app can be downloaded from the Google Play Store.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">But we’re not stopping with Android. We’re hard at work on a version of the app for Windows devices and building in features that will let you send prints of your favorite photos directly to your loved ones. If you have any suggestions for new ways we can help you capture and share cherished moments, please don’t hesitate to let us know.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">As ever, thank you for using 23snaps. We have been absolutely overwhelmed by the positive feedback from the tens of thousands of parents, grandparents, family and friends who have downloaded 23snaps in the last few months. We hope you continue to enjoy using 23snaps to save and treasure those special moments with the children in your life.</p></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Interacting with Content on 23snaps</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37405233429/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 07 Dec 2012 15:16:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37405233429</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Interacting with any of the content posted on 23snaps is unbelievably simple, there’s 2 different ways you can do this &#8230;</p>
<img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_meo28vISkE1rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/>
<p><em><strong>On the App</strong></em></p>
<p><strong>1. Add a comment:</strong><br/>If someone in your network has added a picture or a status that you would like to leave a comment on, all you need to do is:</p>
<ul><li>tap the “add comment’ icon beneath the lower left corner of the image/status</li>
<li>type in your comment</li>
<li>tap the orange “done” button in the top right corner</li>
</ul><p>Your comment will appear right below the content to which it relates.<br/><br/><strong>2. Add a smiley</strong><br/>If you would rather simply show your reaction to a post without leaving a comment, you can post an emoticon on any content with the app.</p>
<ul><li>tap the grey scale heart icon beneath your chosen post</li>
<li>choose between: like, dislike, love or suprised</li>
<li>tap your chosen emoticon and watch it appear beneath the post</li>
</ul><p>Unlike when leaving a comment, your smiley won’t have your name next to it, but if someone presses it they can see who posted it.<img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_meo224jFcf1rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/><br/><br/><em><strong>On the Website:</strong></em><br/><strong>1. Add a comment:</strong></p>
<ul><li>type in your comment in the box beneath the relevant post</li>
<li>click the “comment” button underneath the right corner of the text box</li>
</ul><p>Your comment will appear right below the content to which it relates.<br/><br/><strong>2. Leave a smiley:</strong></p>
<ul><li>locate the grey scale smileys to the left of the image/status</li>
<li>choose between: like, dislike, love or suprised</li>
<li>click on your chosen emoticon</li>
</ul><p>If you are the first person to have posted that particular smiley you will see it change from grey to colour with a little 1 next to it, if someone has already posted that emoticon your post will just increase the number next to the icon. Unlike when leaving a comment, your smiley won’t have your name next to it, but if someone clicks on it they can see who posted it.<br/><strong><br/></strong></p>]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong id="internal-source-marker_0.4281537977512926"><span>Everybody loves a Christmas movie to get them in the festive spirit, here we’ve decided on our top 5 favourite christmas films for the whole family.</span><br/><span></span><br/><span></span><br/><em>The Polar Express</em><br/><span></span><img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mekg4qgMbM1rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/><br/><span>(2004) </span><span>On Christmas Eve, a doubting boy boards a magical train that&#8217;s headed to the North Pole and Santa Claus&#8217;s home.</span><span></span><br/><span></span><br/><span></span></strong></p>

				<title>Travelling with Children</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37550826026/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 09 Dec 2012 13:02:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong><span><img align="middle" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_menuxa3acP1rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/></span></strong></p>
<p><strong id="internal-source-marker_0.1457146112807095"><span>If you’re planning on taking a trip this winter that involves travelling with children, whether  you’re visiting family or maybe just heading off on a fun family vacation? Long journeys with small children can turn out to be a nightmare for the unprepared, so take a look at these handy hints and tips that we’ve found from <em><a href="http://akamommagazine.com/winter-travel/">AKA Mom</a></em> and <em><a href="http://www.techtalkformoms.com/2011/iphone/winter-travel-tips-from-kidzout-com/">Tech Talk for Moms</a></em></span></strong><strong id="internal-source-marker_0.1457146112807095"><span> to get you on your way and make sure everyone enjoys every minute.</span></strong></p>

	<item>
				<title>Good Mobile Phone Photos</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37631363925/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 10 Dec 2012 11:08:52 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37631363925</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_met7u57WtD1rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/>
<p>Now that our mobile phones, and more specifically smartphones, have such good quality cameras already incorporated many of us don’t want to have to carry a camera around with us too. This means we are relying on our mobile phone photos as our main means of capturing a memory. We’ve got a few tips to help you out to ensure you take a better quality pic right on your mobile phone &#8230;<br/><br/><em><strong>Clean your lens</strong></em><br/>A simple thing that most of us forget, but your phone will spend a lot of it’s time in your bag or pocket so wipe the lense to remove any residual dirt.<br/><br/><em><strong>Keep your smartphone steady</strong></em><br/>As a lightweight piece of technology your phone may be subject to jiggling from shaky hands whilst trying to capture your snapshot, leaning against a sturdy surface to steady yourself can work wonders to prevent a blurred photo.<br/><br/><em><strong>Increase your resolution</strong></em><br/>The higher the resolution, the clearer the shot. This also allows you to edit and resize your photo later without losing the clarity.<br/><br/><em><strong>Manual zoom over digital zoom</strong></em><br/>If you’re tempted to zoom in on your subject, we’d recommend you physically move in closer to them rather than zoom with your phone as this can leave the photo out of focus.<br/><br/><em><strong>Vary your angle</strong></em><br/>If you have the time to attempt several shots, try moving around a bit. If the first shot you took wasn’t to your liking, it’s unlikely another shot of the same subject taken from the same angle is gonna do the trick either. Try various different angles and with any luck you will get a few options that you like.<br/><br/><em><strong>Don’t fear the flash</strong></em><br/>Obviously when it’s dark we all rely on a flash to light up our photo subject, but when the natural light just doesn’t cut it, don’t be afraid to turn on your flash, just make sure it doesn’t wash out the image.<br/><br/><em><strong>Learn the shutter speed</strong></em><br/>Make sure you’re aware of how long the delay is between pressing the button and the photo being taken, as that moment can mean missing a beautiful picture.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Calendar View</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37634095011/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 10 Dec 2012 12:47:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37634095011</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>When it comes to viewing a child&#8217;s timeline, there are 2 different options. You can select to view posts as a News Feed or as Calendar View. <br/><span></span><br/><span>To locate the option to view the timeline in Calendar View on the iPhone all you have to do is:</span></p>
<ul><li><span>select the child’s profile </span></li>
<li><span>tap the options bar at the top of the screen to access the drop down menu</span></li>
<li><span>select “Calendar”</span></li>
</ul><p><span>The timeline will reload with the new Calendar View activated.</span></p>
<p><span></span><img alt="image" height="225" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_metewc2pek1rqaa0a.jpg" width="150" alt=""/><span></span>             <img alt="image" height="225" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_metexnEiAZ1rqaa0a.jpg" width="150" alt=""/><img alt="image" height="225" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_metezl3gKx1rqaa0a.jpg" width="150" alt=""/><br/><span></span><br/><span></span></p>
<p><span>To change to the Calendar View on the 23snaps website is even easier, all you have to do is:</span></p>
<ul><li>select the childs profile</li>
<li>click the “Calendar View” option in the top right hand corner of the profile</li>
</ul><p><span>The timeline should instantly reload as the Calendar View.</span></p>
<img alt="image" height="250" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_metfmtBfp01rqaa0a.jpg" width="250" alt=""/>
<img alt="image" height="250" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_metfokvjJW1rqaa0a.png" width="250" alt=""/>]]></content:encoded>

				<title>Perfect Non-Alcoholic Drinks for the Whole Family</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37782368878/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 12 Dec 2012 11:30:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37782368878</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If you&#8217;re looking for some drink ideas this Holiday season but you&#8217;re wanting to go easy on the booze, or you&#8217;re looking for something tasty that the whole family can enjoy, regardless of age, then why not try whipping up some of <a href="http://www.marthastewart.com/274425/nonalcoholic-holiday-drinks/@center/276958/holiday-entertaining#258884">Martha Stewart&#8217;s delicious non-alcoholic cocktails</a>. 	<item>
				<title>Cracking Christmas Photo Tips</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/37901908844/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 14 Dec 2012 11:30:22 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/37901908844</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Here we have some helpful hints and tips for taking great holiday themed photos of your children over the festive period.</p>
<img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_meii6nEt1Q1rqaa0a.jpg" alt=""/>
<p><em><strong>Festive attire: </strong></em></p>
<p>A santa hat, some reindeer antlers or even just a carrot nose. Taking a fantastic festive photos really boils down to theprops. A photo of your child taken at any time of year will always be precious, but if you want to add some christmas cheer and take some holiday photos to treasure forever, you have to turn up the volume on the “festive” side slightly more than you would normally do day to day. You might not want to take a miniature Santa Claus to the supermarket with you, but it will be super cute to have one on your family’s holiday card this year. Grab those christmas outfits, props and decorations and off you go</p>

<img alt="image" height="200" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_meiht40Xc01rqaa0a.jpg" width="250" alt=""/>
<p><em><strong>Cut the cheese:</strong> </em></p>
<p>Stop asking your child to SAY CHEESE! Since when does anyone smile naturally with their lips pulled back over their teeth in a terrifying grimace? (OK, maybe I did a few times during my childhood but that was only when I wanted to scare my parents into buying me something). Just let them carry on with whatever they were up to anyway, your photos will look much more realistic and less like you’ve been attempting to set up the image for the past hour.</p>

<img alt="image" height="200" src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_meihzqAhK91rqaa0a.jpg" width="250" alt=""/>
<p><em><strong>Stop Fishing:</strong></em></p>
<p>You will always be able to snap your baby looking happier if you aren’t deliberately trying to &#8220;catch&#8221; their attention, they might not be in the mood to look patiently into the camera. All you need to do is position yourself to be somewhere within their line of vision, a photo of a profile can be just as beautiful as a straight on image. Although … try to avoid continually snapping pictures of the back of your little ones head, it might be beautiful to you but it could get a little old if you want to show off your photographic prowess to your friends.</p>]]></content:encoded>

				<title>Top 10 Xmas gift ideas for babies and toddlers</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/38058800398/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 16 Dec 2012 13:03:19 +0000</pubDate>

	<item>
				<title>A Tribute to Moms - &quot;When God Created Mothers&quot;</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/38942062675/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 27 Dec 2012 10:30:39 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/38942062675</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>
<p>For all the hardworking moms over the festive period; you are very much appreciated!</p>

</div>
<div>
<div>
<blockquote>
<p><em>When the Good Lord was creating mothers, He was into His sixth day of &#8220;overtime&#8221; when the angel appeared and said. &#8220;You&#8217;re doing a lot of fiddling around on this one.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>And God said, &#8220;Have you read the specs on this order?&#8221; She has to be completely washable, but not plastic. Have 180 moveable parts&#8230;all replaceable. Run on black coffee and leftovers. Have a lap that disappears when she stands up. A kiss that can cure anything from a broken leg to a disappointed love affair. And six pairs of hands.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>The angel shook her head slowly and said. &#8220;Six pairs of hands&#8230;. no way.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>It&#8217;s not the hands that are causing me problems,&#8221; God remarked, &#8220;it&#8217;s the three pairs of eyes that mothers have to have.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>That&#8217;s on the standard model?&#8221; asked the angel. God nodded. </em><br/><br/><em>One pair that sees through closed doors when she asks, &#8216;What are you kids doing in there?&#8217; when she already knows. Another here in the back of her head that sees what she shouldn&#8217;t but what she has to know, and of course the ones here in front that can look at a child when he goofs up and say. &#8216;I understand and I love you&#8217; without so much as uttering a word.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>God,&#8221; said the angel touching his sleeve gently, &#8220;Get some rest tomorrow&#8230;.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>I can&#8217;t,&#8221; said God, &#8220;I&#8217;m so close to creating something so close to myself. Already I have one who heals herself when she is sick&#8230;can feed a family of six on one pound of hamburger&#8230;and can get a nine year old to stand under a shower.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>The angel circled the model of a mother very slowly. &#8220;It&#8217;s too soft,&#8221; she sighed. </em><br/><br/><em>But tough!&#8221; said God excitedly. &#8220;You can imagine what this mother can do or endure.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>Can it think?&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>Not only can it think, but it can reason and compromise,&#8221; said the Creator. </em><br/><br/><em>Finally, the angel bent over and ran her finger across the cheek. </em><br/><br/><em>There&#8217;s a leak,&#8221; she pronounced. &#8220;I told You that You were trying to put too much into this model.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>It&#8217;s not a leak,&#8221; said the Lord, &#8220;It&#8217;s a tear.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>What&#8217;s it for?&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>It&#8217;s for joy, sadness, disappointment, pain, loneliness, and pride.&#8221; </em><br/><br/><em>You are a genius, &#8221; said the angel. </em><br/><br/><em>Somberly, God said, &#8220;I didn&#8217;t put it there.”</em></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong><em>Erma Bombeck</em> (When God Created Mothers)</strong></p>]]></content:encoded>

				<title>Mommy Time Savers</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/39740093517/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 05 Jan 2013 12:00:53 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[23snaps]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/post/39740093517</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span>Ever felt like maybe if you just had a few more hours in the day, you could truly become a </span><em>“SuperMom”</em><span>? Get everything done in a perfect manner? It’s a shame that we just don’t have any more time …. well check out these </span><a href="http://www.momagenda.com/mommy-time-savers/">time saving tips from MomAgenda</a><span> that could save you the equivalent of SEVEN WEEKS A YEAR!! </span></p>

		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>39740093517</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2013-01-05 13:00:53</wp:post_date>

	<item>
				<title>Help with 23snaps</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/help-with-23snaps/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 14 Jan 2013 12:00:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://devblog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093525</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/help-with-23snaps/zendesk-blog-post-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093601"><img class="size-medium wp-image-39740093601 alignleft" alt="zendesk blog post" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/zendesk-blog-post1-300x169.jpg" width="300" height="169" /></a>
<p style="text-align: left;">So we here at 23snaps HQ have been glued to the app for the last week in order to identify any possible questions you might have when it comes to using 23snaps as we want to provide you with some really simple and easy to follow guides on how to use all of our features. If there are any processes in the app that you’re struggling with or you just want a little bit more knowledge on how it can be used, we now have a <em><a title="Zendesk" href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/home">23snaps support forum</a></em> where all your questions will be answered. However, if there is anything that you can’t find the answer to you can still drop us a line directly through the forum and we will be happy to help in any way that we can. Now everyone can be an expert in 23snaps!</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><em> </em></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Uploading a photo to 23snaps: A How To Guide.</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/uploading-a-photo-to-23snaps/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 16 Jan 2013 11:20:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://devblog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093581</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h3><em> </em></h3>
One of the first things you need to get familiar with when using 23snaps is how to upload a photo; here is our How To guide complete with images for an easy, step by step instruction on how to post photos in your account.
<h3><em>On the website</em></h3>
Click on the <em style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Newsfeed</em> tab at the top of the page (this is the homescreen so you may already be there), then hit the orange <em style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Add Photos</em> button at the top of your newsfeed. You will then be given the following options to choose from:
<ul>
	<li>Upload from computer</li>
	<li>Facebook</li>
	<li>Flikr</li>
	<li>Picassa</li>
	<li>Instagram</li>
</ul>
Choose your preferred application, locate the photo(s) you wish to upload and click <em>open</em>. You will be prompted to <em>use selected</em> photo(s), then you can add a description to the photo, tag your child and decide when on the timeline it should appear. Finally click on the blue <em>submit</em> button to upload your photo(s).

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/uploading-a-photo-to-23snaps/web-add-a-photo-landscape/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093583"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740093583" alt="web - add a photo landscape" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/web-add-a-photo-landscape.png" width="1976" height="272" /></a>
<h3></h3>
<h3><em>On the app</em></h3>
Click on the orange button in the top right corner; you will be given the option of adding a photo, video, status or measurement - tap the <em>photo</em> icon. You can then choose whether to take a photo or to choose from your library. Once you have selected the photo you want to upload, you can apply filters, add a description, tag your child and decide when on the timeline it should appear. Then tap the orange <em>Publish</em> button in the top right hand corner and your photo will be uploaded to 23snaps.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/uploading-a-photo-to-23snaps/app-photo-final-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093582"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-39740093582" alt="App photo final - 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/App-photo-final-2.jpg" width="1328" height="485" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps as a SCRAPBOOK as well as a PHOTOBOOK!</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-as-a-scrapbook-as-well-as-a-photobook/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 20 Jan 2013 01:30:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://devblog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093591</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-as-a-scrapbook-as-well-as-a-photobook/scrapbook/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093592"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-39740093592" alt="scrapbook" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/scrapbook.jpg" width="239" height="202" /></a></p>
23snaps was designed as a way to share your photos with close friends and family in a private and secure environment, the app allows you to build an online baby book simply bursting with the photos you capture of your children everyday. But what about everything else involved in your child's life, don't you want to document that too? The hospital bracelet your baby was wearing when you brought them home, the first pair of shoes that they grew out of and the painting that your little one did for you at nursery, why not take photos of all of these things and use 23snaps as a scrapbook as well as a photobook. Instead of putting these things into a box where you will never look at them, simply snap a photo and upload it to your child's timeline, then you can go back and enjoy all of the little things again and agan.

<img class=" wp-image-39740093594 alignright" alt="baby shoes" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/baby-shoes-300x199.jpg" width="270" height="179" /><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-as-a-scrapbook-as-well-as-a-photobook/baby-shoes/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093594"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-as-a-scrapbook-as-well-as-a-photobook/childs-painting-of-a-house_2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093593"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-39740093593" alt="child's painting of a house_2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/childs-painting-of-a-house_2-300x154.jpg" width="300" height="154" /></a>
</a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps photo filters: perfect for pictures of your children.</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-filters-perfect-for-pictures-of-your-children/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 21 Jan 2013 01:00:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093623</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[When developing 23snaps we knew that we definitely wanted to include photo filters, but in order to carve out our own niche; we wanted to provide filters with specific attributes that made them the best filters to use on photos of children. So we set to work experimenting with some of the existing photo filters out there and we discovered something … a lot of these existing filters can leave your child looking ‘not of this world’. We realized that in order to appeal to parents, we would have to design our own filters that would enhance their photos rather than providing those that might mean your beautiful, bouncing baby is going to end up looking somewhat sickly with a slightly green tinge.

Time and effort was put into designing and testing a variety of different filters to ensure that we only used those that would work well with the type of photos specific to our users. We wanted to smooth out skin tones instead of creating more of a rough look, we also wanted to remove any filters with particular color tints that might clash with that lovely, almost translucent quality that babies’ skin has. We honestly just wanted to make the photos of your children even better.
<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-39740093624" alt="filters blog" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/filters-blog.jpg" width="1468" height="642" />We are continuously working on all of the features of 23snaps and we have in no way finished developing our filters, but we wanted to share with you exactly how important it is to us that you absolutely love the photos that you upload to 23snaps. We hope that by explaining how and why we chose the filters that we have will give all of our users an indication of how much thought goes into 23snaps. It was designed by parents after all!

If you want to know how to make use of this feature of 23snaps you can go to our simple, illustrated <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/entries/22604566-how-do-i-use-photo-filters">How To guide</a>.

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps is easy and accessible for anyone to use.</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-is-easy-and-accessible-for-anyone-to-use/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 23 Jan 2013 12:00:21 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093628</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-39740093629" alt="fml-grandma-computer" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/fml-grandma-computer.jpg" width="250" height="216" />

When our founders came up with the idea for 23snaps, there was one thing that they knew wanted… this app had to be accessible to EVERYONE. There would be no point in designing an amazing looking but super complicated photo sharing app if only the most tech savvy among us could figure out how to use it and view those photos. 23snaps is a beautifully designed yet incredibly simple app to use, that way if you want to share your children’s photo’s with their grandparents who may not be at the most technologically minded of people, they would still be able to use and appreciate all of the features we took the time to include. Although uploading photos still remains the exclusive right of the parents, we have ensured that the processes for commenting on and liking photos, as well saving images to your computer are incredibly uncomplicated.

We also wanted to make sure we wouldn’t exclude the non-smartphone owners from enjoying 23snaps, which is why an account with us can be managed solely from the website. We are continuously working on features of the website and to ensure it is as interactive as the app.

So please don’t hesitate to invite any of your family to connect based on the assumption that they might not be able to manage an account, we have made sure that Grandma can get just as involved with 23snaps as anybody else!]]></content:encoded>

				<title>Taking beautiful photos of your children</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/39740093658/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 26 Jan 2013 12:30:11 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>

				<title>Kate&#039;s bikini bump</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/kates-bikini-bump/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 Feb 2013 16:23:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093695</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Oh dear, yet again the paparazzi have managed to annoy the royal parents-to-be. Whilst trying to relax in a luxury villa on the island of Mustique last week, Kate was snapped showing off her baby bump in a bikini whilst on the beach with her husband, and our future monarch, Prince William. A palace source has stated that they feel violated. We're not sure it's as big of an issue as the royals seem to think it is, we're sure Kate looked as lovely as usual, but who are we to decide what pictures she should want out there for the world to see?

Maybe this will prove to Will and Kate exactly how important maintaining their child's provacy will be to them, so they should probably download 23snaps now to make absolutely sure all of their photos involving Baby Royal are completely safe!]]></content:encoded>
