	<item>
				<title>23snaps; photo editing features.</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 06 Mar 2013 16:18:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093772</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<strong><em>Photo Filters</em></strong>
23snaps provides photo filters with specific attributes that make them the best filters to use on photos of children. There are the classic filters that allow you to change the photo be black and white or apply a sepia effect, but we have also developed our own filters that can smooth out skin tones and apply particular color tints that work really beautifully in combination with a babies’ skin tone. We honestly just want to make the photos of your children even better.

<a style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;" href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093774"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093773" alt="photo 1" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-1-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <a style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;" href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093774"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093774" alt="photo 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-2-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <a style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;" href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-3/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093775"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093775" alt="photo 3" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-3-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <a style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;" href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-4/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093776"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093776" alt="photo 4" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-4-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <em style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">                        Original                                        Cream                                           Endell                                           Retro  </em>

<strong><em>Vignettes</em></strong>
A vignette creates a loss of clarity towards the corners and sides of an image. By applying one of three different gradients of vignette to an image you can highlight the main feature of the photo, this way you will instantly draw attention to your child’s beautiful smiling face. This can be used if there are lots of things happening in the background of the image, you can effectively draw focus to the child(ren) in the image by reducing the clarity of the things around them.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-1-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093773"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093773" alt="photo 1" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-1-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093777" style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1;" alt="photo 5" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-5-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /> <a style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;" href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-1-1/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093783"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093783" alt="photo 1 (1)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-1-1-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-2-1/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093785"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093785" alt="photo 2 (1)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-2-1-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<em style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Original                                          Small                                           Medium                                         Large  </em>

<em><strong>Frames</strong></em>
In order to inspire individuality when uploading your photos, we have provided a selection of different frames that can be applied to your image. These include basic black and white borders, as well as a more retro looking polaroid frame that will make your image look like it was snapped with the old style camera. This is just one more way that allows parents to be creative when building their child’s digital journal.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-1-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093773"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093773" alt="photo 1" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-1-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-3-1/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093797"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093797" alt="photo 3 (1)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-3-1-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-4-1/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093798"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093798" alt="photo 4 (1)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-4-1-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-editing-features/photo-5-1/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093799"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-39740093799" alt="photo 5 (1)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-5-1-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<em style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Original                                          Luma                                           Distressed                                    Polaroid  </em>

<em>If you would like any help on how to use these features, it can be found on our <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/entries/22604566-How-do-I-use-photo-filters-and-photo-editing-features-">helpdesk</a>.</em>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps; Profile View Layouts</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-profile-view-layouts/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Mar 2013 11:22:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093827</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b id="internal-source-marker_0.5534881958737969"><em><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-profile-view-layouts/aiden-calender-view/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093828"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-39740093828" alt="Aiden Calender View" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Aiden-Calender-View-201x300.jpg" width="201" height="300" /></a></em></b>

&nbsp;

<strong><em>Calendar View</em></strong>

This layout will organise all of the content uploaded to a child’s profile so that you can view a full month at a time, in date   order. The images, videos, statuses and measurements are displayed in small boxes which will allow you to see more of the content at one time.<b id="internal-source-marker_0.5534881958737969"></b>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<img class="size-medium wp-image-39740093829 alignleft" alt="Screen Shot 2013-03-07 at 10.33.13" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Screen-Shot-2013-03-07-at-10.33.13-300x270.png" width="300" height="270" />

&nbsp;

<strong><em>Timeline View</em></strong>

The timeline view displays all of a child’s uploads in a long list, which will show the most recent at the top (remember, if your photo has a timestamp, this is the date that 23snaps will recognise, not the date of upload, unless you edit it accordingly).
<b id="internal-source-marker_0.5534881958737969">
</b>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-profile-view-layouts/photo/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093830"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-39740093830" alt="photo" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-200x300.png" width="200" height="300" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<strong><em>Gallery View</em></strong> <em style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">(Currently only available on IOS)</em>

This view will display all of a childs content, as a collage, on one screen. This gives you great access if you want to look for one image in particular, as they are all in one place.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<em>If you would like any help on how to use these features, it can be found on our <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/entries/22875412-What-are-the-Timeline-Calendar-and-Gallery-views-for-a-child-s-profile-and-how-do-I-switch-between-t">helpdesk</a>.</em>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps; Sharing to Other Social Platforms</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-sharing-to-other-social-platforms-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 09 Mar 2013 12:45:09 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093847</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<em><strong>Sharing to Facebook</strong></em>
Although one of the main priorities of 23snaps is to ensure you have a completely secure platform in which to share your photos, occasionally you may decide there is a photo or a video that you just cannot resist sharing to Facebook to show the masses. You can either choose to upload your content to Facebook and 23snaps simultaneously, whilst posting on your child’s timeline. Alternatively you have the option to go back to something that you posted previously and share it, the post will appear in your Facebook timeline immediately.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093848" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093848"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740093848" alt="photo 1 (2)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-1-2-200x300.png" width="98" height="147" /></a>     <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093849" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093849"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740093849" alt="photo 2 (2)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-2-2-200x300.png" width="98" height="147" /></a>     <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093850" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093850"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740093850" alt="photo 3 (2)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-3-2-199x300.png" width="97" height="147" /></a>
<em><strong>Sharing by Email</strong></em>
Although all of your connections have the option to receive email digests of any content you upload to your 23snaps account, perhaps there is one particular image you want to ensure they see? Maybe some of your friends and family have not yet had the opportunity to set up their own account and you don’t want them to miss out on the insanely adorable photo you just uploaded? You can very easily send them individual uploads straight from your Newsfeed.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093848" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093848"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740093848" alt="photo 1 (2)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-1-2-200x300.png" width="98" height="147" /></a>     <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093849" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093849"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740093849" alt="photo 2 (2)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-2-2-200x300.png" width="98" height="147" /></a>     <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093851" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093851"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740093851" alt="photo 4 (2)" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-4-2-200x300.png" width="98" height="147" /></a>

&nbsp;

<em>If you would like any help sharing content with either <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/entries/22601963-Can-I-post-an-update-from-23snaps-to-Facebook-">Facebook</a> or <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/entries/22601307-Can-I-share-an-update-I-ve-posted-with-someone-who-doesn-t-use-23snaps-">email</a>, it can be found on our <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/forums">helpdesk</a>.</em>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Happy Mother&#039;s Day (UK) - Simnel Cake Recipe</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/happy-mothers-day-uk-simnel-cake-recipe/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 10 Mar 2013 10:00:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093871</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p align="center"><b>Traditional British Mothering Sunday Simnel Cake Recipe</b></p>
&nbsp;

<b>Ingredients: <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/mothers-day-in-the-uk-simnel-cake-recipe/simnel-cake-slice-photo-credit-james-e-petts/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093864"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-39740093864" alt="Simnel Cake Slice – photo credit James E Petts" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Simnel-Cake-Slice-–-photo-credit-James-E-Petts-225x300.jpg" width="225" height="300" /></a>
</b>¾ cup sugar
3 cups mixed dried fruit (such as cherries, apricots, pineapple, raisins, golden raisins and lemon peel)
5 tbs orange liquor (such as Grand Marnier or Cointreau)
1 ½ stick unsalted butter, room temperature
4 pieces stem singer from a jar, finely chopped.
3 eggs
1 ½ cups flour
1 tsp ground nutmeg
1 tsp ground cinnamon
1 tsp ground cloves
1lb white marzipan
2-3 tbs apricot or orange jam
Powdered sugar (for decoration)

<b>Instructions:</b>
<ol>
	<li>Preheat the oven to 310F and grease and line an 8in cake pan. 1 Place the dried fruit in a bowl and add the liquor. Let soak for about an hour.</li>
	<li>Chop the butter into squares and add butter, ginger and sugar to a fitted mixing bowl. Beat on medium speed until pale and creamy. Gradually add in the eggs. When they are fully incorporated, remove from the mixer and fold in the flour and spices, then the dried fruit, along with with any juices left in the bowl. Mix well.</li>
	<li>Take half the marzipan and place on a surface dusted with powdered sugar. Roll the marzipan into an 8" circle and set aside. Repeat with the remaining half of the marzipan.</li>
	<li>Spoon half of the cake mixture into the cake tin and level the top with a spoon. Place one of the marzipan rounds onto of the cake mixture and press down gently. Spoon the remaining cake mixture into the cake tin and level the top.</li>
	<li>Bake for between 2 hours and 15 minutes and 2 hours and 30 minutes or until a skewer comes out clean. Let the cake cool in the tin for at least 20-30 minutes but leave the oven on and change the setting to broil.</li>
	<li>Remove the cake from tin and spread the apricot or orange jam then place the second marzipan round on top. Press down gently to seal to the cake. Place the cake back in the oven for 1-2 minutes under the broiler, until the marzipan starts to toast. Remove when the marzipan on top turns a golden brown.</li>
	<li>Let cool and serve, dusting with additional powdered sugar or marzipan balls if desired.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps; Managing Multiple Childrens&#039; Accounts</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-managing-multiple-childrens-accounts/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 16 Mar 2013 12:00:36 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093888</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We know that as parent's you want to share the individuality of each of your children, you shouldn't have to lump them all in together when the each have their very own personality. That is why we have enabled you to choose, for each individual post, which of your children you want to include. They may not all be going to tumble tots at the same time, maybe only one child is involved in that dance recital? Why shouldn't you be able to show off all of your child's individual characteristics without alienating your other children? With 23snaps we make it unbelievably simple to share photos, videos and updates to just one, a selection of, or ALL of your children in one go. All you have to do, when uploading your content, is select which child(ren) you wish to tag by clicking on their thumbnail image. It couldn't be easier right?!

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093889" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093889"><img class=" wp-image-39740093889 alignleft" alt="Managing multiple kids 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Managing-multiple-kids-2-193x300.jpg" width="154" height="240" /></a><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093890" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093890"><img class=" wp-image-39740093890 alignleft" alt="Managing multiple kids" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Managing-multiple-kids-190x300.jpg" width="152" height="240" /></a>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps; Uploading Various Types of Content</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/39740093917/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 21 Mar 2013 16:23:30 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093917</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr"><strong><em>Videos<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-uploading-various-types-of-content/features-videos/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093906"><img class=" wp-image-39740093906 alignleft" alt="23snaps features - videos" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/features-videos-194x300.jpg" width="124" height="192" /></a>
</em></strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">There are very few photo sharing apps that allow you to post both photos AND videos, but we here at 23snaps didn’t want to stifle the types of things you would want to share. In the same way that you can post photos of your children to their timelines, you can also post 30 second videos capturing special moments in your kids lives.</p>
<b><b> </b></b>
<p dir="ltr"><strong><em>Status Updates<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-uploading-various-types-of-content/feature-status/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093909"><img class=" wp-image-39740093909 alignleft" alt="23snaps features - status" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/feature-status-195x300.jpg" width="124" height="192" /></a></em></strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">You may not always have a video or photo that you wish to share, but you can still keep all of your connections updated with what your little one is up to by posting status updates. This feature allows you to post short descriptions of trips, activities and milestones so that your friends and family don’t miss a moment.</p>
<b><b> </b></b><b><b>
</b></b>
<p dir="ltr"><em><strong>Height &amp; Weight Measurements<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-uploading-various-types-of-content/features-measurement/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093907"><img class=" wp-image-39740093907 alignleft" alt="features - measurement" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/features-measurement-195x300.jpg" width="124" height="192" /></a></strong></em></p>
<p dir="ltr">Do you have family far away? We think that even if they don’t get to see your children all the time, they’d still love to see how quickly they shoot up in height! And everybody always wants to know the weight of a newborn baby. It’s for this reason that we have a specific measurement feature that allows you to post height and weight measurements in either metric or imperial units.</p>

<b><b> </b></b>
<b><b> </b></b>
<b><b> </b></b>
<b><b> </b></b>
<b><b> </b></b>
<b><b> </b></b>]]></content:encoded>

That means if you want to upload 10 photos a day from the day your bouncing baby is born right up until their 18th birthday, there is absolutely nothing that will stand in your way!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Brand new website!</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/brand-new-website/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 29 Mar 2013 14:30:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740093947</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://23snaps.com">23snaps.com</a> has a whole new look! It’s all very exciting!

&nbsp;

<img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-39740093948" alt="New website child's profile" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/New-website-childs-profile-1024x505.jpg" width="625" height="308" />

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

We have completely redesigned the 23snaps website and now it is absolutely beautiful. There are a huge amount more features accessible through the site that until now had only been available on the app, a few of which include posting photos, status updates AND measurements directly from your computer. You can also access an entire families profile, change wallpapers and manage all of your email digests and notifications.

&nbsp;

<img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-39740093950" alt="New website newsfeed" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/New-website-newsfeed-1024x507.jpg" width="625" height="309" />

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

We are passionate about making our app accessible for the whole family, so we know we need to be more than just a smartphone app. One of the main reasons that we have rebuilt our website is specifically to allow all generations to utilise 23snaps regardless of their level of tech knowledge. A lot of existing digital services aimed at families are difficult for less tech-savvy family members to use and understand, we refuse to follow suit. The new website is really simple to navigate, but if for any reason you do get a little bit stuck, we’ve also updated our helpdesk to provide assistance and answers to any of the questions you might have.

&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740093949" rel="attachment wp-att-39740093949"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-39740093949" alt="New website family &amp; friends" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/New-website-family-friends-1024x504.png" width="625" height="307" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

What are you waiting for? Go <a href="http://23snaps.com">check it out</a>!!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Spring Bingo - Colouring activities for children</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/spring-bingo-colouring-activities-for-children/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 10 Apr 2013 09:35:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094004</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Spring Bingo is a great activity to keep your kids entertained - <em>maximum 5 players.</em>

To play this game all you need to do is print out all of the bingo sheets, take one and cut out all of the individual squares. Pass the remaining sheets out to all the players (each child should have a different sheet)

Place the cut out pictures into a hat or bowl, pull them out one at a time (just as you would with bingo numbers).

Each time a square is pulled from the hat/bowl, each player must colour their corresponding picture.

The first to fill in a line either vertically or horizontally wins the game!

<a href="http://www.crayola.com/free-coloring-pages/print/spring-bingo-5-coloring-page/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094008"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-39740094008" alt="Screen Shot href="http://www.crayola.com/free-coloring-pages/print/spring-bingo-4-coloring-page/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094007"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-39740094007" alt="Screen Shot 2013-04-10 at 10.14.56" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Screen-Shot-2013-04-10-at-10.14.56-150x150.png" width="150" height="150" /></a> <a 				<title>23snaps; Email Digests</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-email-digests/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 18 Apr 2013 10:10:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094020</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-email-digests/email-digests-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094024"><img class="alignright  wp-image-39740094024" alt="Email Digests" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Email-Digests1-565x1024.jpg" width="271" height="491" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr">When you use 23snaps you will receive beautifully presented email digests containing all of the content uploaded by the friends and family you connect with. You can choose to receive your digests either in real-time for each individual upload, or if you prefer you can set the frequency to daily or weekly. If you choose weekly you can even decide which day of the week you want them to arrive!</p>
<b><b> </b></b>
<p dir="ltr">You’ll never miss a thing when you know without a doubt that you will receive every photo, video and update uploaded by your connections right to your inbox.</p>

				<title>Saying Sorry To Your Kids</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/saying-sorry-to-your-kids/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 25 Apr 2013 13:49:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094039</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We've just been directed to this brilliant blog post over at GoNannies.com, and we wanted to share it. They've discussed real reasons for needing to apologise to your children from time to time, and why you shouldn't be afraid to say you're sorry. Click <a href="http://www.gonannies.com/blog/2013/4-reasons-to-say-im-sorry-to-your-children/">here</a> to check it out.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/saying-sorry-to-your-kids/23snaps-saying-youre-sorry/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094040"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-39740094040" alt="23snaps; Saying you're sorry." src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/23snaps-Saying-youre-sorry..jpg" width="849" height="566" /></a>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps; your online baby book - save your baby&#039;s firsts</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-your-online-baby-book-save-your-babys-firsts/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 26 Apr 2013 10:23:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094043</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[One of our lovely mommy users recently asked "is there any way for me to document all of my baby's firsts, like you would in a physical baby book?". We were very pleased to tell her that yes! there is a very simple way to organise all of your little ones milestones into one easy to navigate album. But then we thought, if we're being asked this now, is this something that our users are unaware of? Oh dear! So we're writing this post to provide instructions and inspiration for creating a beautiful album entirely dedicated to those first words, first steps and first everything elses.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-your-online-baby-book-save-your-babys-firsts/23snaps-firsts-collection/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094048"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094048" style="margin-right: 15px;" alt="23snaps; Firsts Collection" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/23snaps-Firsts-Collection-150x150.jpg" width="190" height="190" /></a>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-your-online-baby-book-save-your-babys-firsts/23snaps-first-steps/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094046"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094046" style="margin-right: 15px;" alt="23snaps; First Steps" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/23snaps-First-Steps-150x150.jpg" width="190" height="190" /></a><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-your-online-baby-book-save-your-babys-firsts/200301769-001/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094047"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094047" alt="200301769-001" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/23snaps-First-Tooth-150x150.jpg" width="190" height="190" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

When you first register an account with 23snaps, there are a few collections already set up for you by default. You can change these to be titled however you like, but we have got a "Firsts" collection all ready for you.

You can organise all of your child's firsts to appear in this collection whether you use the iOS, Android or web application. You can find simple instructions (with screenshots) on how to do so <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/entries/22923568-How-do-I-add-photos-videos-or-updates-to-a-Collection-">here</a>.

To make sure you don't miss a single thing, we've got a fairly comprehensive list of all of the firsts your child will experience:

Baby is born
1st feed
Baby is brought home
Meeting siblings for the first time
1st visit with Grandparents
1st bottle
1st bath
1st time recognizing Mom
1st time recognizing Dad
1st smile
1st laugh
1st time holding head up alone
1st sleep through the night
1st time recognizing brother/sister
1st time rolling over
1st baby food
1st fruit
1st veg
1st word
1st "dada"
1st "mama"
1st outing
1st haircut
Height &amp; weight from the doctors visit
1st wave
1st time sitting up alone
1st time pushes up
1st crawl
1st time standing alone
1st step
1st walk
1 months old
2 months old
3 months old
4 months old
5 months old
6 months old
7 months old
8 months old
9 months old
10 months old
11 months old
1st birthday

This is obviously not a definitive list, there are probably many more firsts that you also want to capture. But with the use of photo, video and text updates there's no reason why every single first can forever be preserved in this beautiful digital journal.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps; Collections</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-collections/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 30 Apr 2013 09:55:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094132</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr">With 23snaps it’s easy to take so many pictures of your little one that favorite photos can get lost.</p>
<p dir="ltr">This is why we introduced Collections, a really simple way to organize and treasure your photos. Collections are like photo albums where you can save related photos, videos and status updates – with just a few unique features that make them much better than your average album!</p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-collections/23snaps-collections/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094133"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-39740094133" alt="23snaps; Collections" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/23snaps-Collections.jpg" width="772" height="752" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr">You can create custom albums to suit your own specific requirements. Create your own inspired collections for Firsts, Favorites, Best Smiles, Holidays, and anything else you want to highlight. There is no limit to the amount of collections you can have, and with the ability to add videos and status updates too; you can really tell the full story.</p>
<p dir="ltr">You don’t have to pick and choose where your pictures belong – add your content to multiple collections so it’s always in the right place.</p>
<p dir="ltr">And the very best feature? You can share your collections with anyone - even people that you aren’t connected with on 23snaps! Simply open up your Collection in the mobile app and choose to “Share via e-mail” – we’ll then send them a sample of the photos and a unique link to access the rest of the collection online. So simple.</p>
<p dir="ltr">If you want to get started creating your Collections, we have a simple <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/entries/22899212-How-do-I-create-a-Collection-">How-To guide</a> to help.</p>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps; Uploading Timestamped Photos</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-uploading-timestamped-photos/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 08 May 2013 13:49:51 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094160</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We know that being a parent means you’re super busy, which might might mean that sometimes you don’t get the opportunity to share the photos you take right away. We understand that it’s not really feasible to expect our busy users to <strong><em>immediately</em></strong> upload all of those gorgeous photos to 23snaps for friends and family to see. That's why our app automatically recognises the timestamp embedded in the photo, so even if you don’t get the chance to upload your images for a day, a week or even a year after it was originally taken, you don’t have to rack your brain to remember the date, as 23snaps will set it for you!

&nbsp;

<b id="docs-internal-guid-6786fcda-8442-142e-4707-d1d4a359c378"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-uploading-timestamped-photos/23snaps-timestamp/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094161"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-39740094161" alt="23snaps; Timestamp" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-Timestamp.jpg" width="1474" height="1292" /></a></b>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Guest Post; How to Determine if Your Child is Left or Right Handed</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/how-to-determine-if-your-child-is-left-or-right-handed/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 13 May 2013 15:38:54 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094199</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[As you watch your child grow, you may be interested in knowing how to determine whether your child is left-handed or right-handed. Some people may feel that it doesn’t matter, but being aware of your child's hand dominance can help you make some small adjustments that could help your child in a variety of situations.

This fantastic article posted to the <a href="http://www.backupcare.org/">backup care</a> website points out some early indicators to help your determine the handedness of your child. To check out the article, click <a href="http://www.backupcare.org/blog/how-to-determine-if-your-child-is-left-or-right-handed/">here</a>.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/how-to-determine-if-your-child-is-left-or-right-handed/23snaps-hand-dominance/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094200"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-39740094200" alt="23snaps; Hand Dominance" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-Hand-Dominance.jpg" width="800" height="507" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps; Photo Printing AND Windows8</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-printing-and-windows8/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 10 May 2013 11:22:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094203</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Wow! This week has been crazy exciting for us here at 23snaps HQ. Not only have we launched our new printing feature, we've also released our newest version of the 23snaps app - compatible with Surface and Windows8 computers (<em>see below for more info</em>).

If that's not all, we've once again been featured in the Lifestyle section of the app store!

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-printing-and-windows8/back-in-the-app-store/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094205"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-39740094205" style="margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;" alt="23snaps; back in the app store" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/back-in-the-app-store-300x182.png" width="300" height="182" /></a>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-printing-and-windows8/photo-4-3/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094204"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094204" style="margin-left: 40px; margin-right: 40px;" alt="23snaps; back in the app store 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/photo-4-199x300.png" width="159" height="240" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

So we're a group of very happy bunnies here at 23snaps. We hope you enjoy all of the new stuff we've got for you, and remember; we LOVE hearing from our users about what they think of 23snaps so please <a href="mailto:support@23snaps.com ">get in touch</a> if you have anything you'd like to say!

&nbsp;

<em><strong>Printing</strong></em>
<p dir="ltr">With the newest <a href="http://app.appsflyer.com/id526481189?pid=blog&amp;c=printing">iOS update of the 23snaps</a> online photobook app, you can now order prints and physical photobooks to treasure forever.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><em>Photobooks:</em></p>
<p dir="ltr">Our beautiful, hardcover photobooks require a minimum of 24 photos and prices start from approximately £15.99 ($23.99). These delightful books can be shipped to anywhere in the world and the shipping costs are included in the price - that’s unbelievable value!</p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-printing-and-windows8/printing-products-1/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094211"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094211" alt="23snaps; printing products 1" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Printing-Products-1-300x189.jpg" width="243" height="153" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr"><em><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-printing-and-windows8/printing-products-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094212"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094212" style="margin-left: 40px; margin-right: 40px;" alt="Printing Products 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Printing-Products-2-300x191.jpg" width="243" height="155" /></a></em></p>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr"><em>Photo Prints:</em></p>
<p dir="ltr">Our high quality photo prints require a minimum order of 10 photos and prices start from approximately £4.49 ($6.99). At this time our photo prints can only be shipped to the UK and USA - but don’t worry, we’re working on providing this service to all of our users as soon as we can!</p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-photo-printing-and-windows8/printing-products-3/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094213"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094213" alt="Printing Products 3" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Printing-Products-3-300x191.jpg" width="240" height="153" /></a></p>

				<title>Guest Post; The Importance of Well Visits in Pediatrics</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/the-importance-of-well-visits-in-pediatrics/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 20 May 2013 08:47:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094251</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/the-importance-of-well-visits-in-pediatrics/23snaps-pediatrician-and-baby/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094252"><img class="size-full wp-image-39740094252 aligncenter" alt="23snaps; pediatrician and baby" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-pediatrician-and-baby.jpg" width="425" height="282" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">As a parent, you understand that visits to the pediatrician are essential when your child is sick or exhibiting symptoms of a medical condition. When they're feeling healthy, however, carving time out of your busy schedule to make and keep well-child appointments can seem like a bit of a waste. There are plenty of reasons why well visits are essential, though. Before you put off that next well-child visit, these are just a few of the reasons why you might want to reconsider postponing it ...</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">To continue reading this brilliantly informative article from the <a href="http://www.liveinnanny.org/blog/">Live In Nanny</a> blog, click <a href="http://www.liveinnanny.org/blog/the-importance-of-well-visits-in-pediatrics/">here</a>.</p>

				<title>How to Set Real World Limits Around Kids and Tech</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/how-to-set-real-world-limits-around-kids-and-tech/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 22 May 2013 09:21:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094278</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We were directed to this article on the <a href="http://www.nannyjobs.net/blog/how-to-set-real-world-limits-around-kids-and-tech/">Nanny Jobs</a> blog and decided we wanted to share it with you. Balancing the amount of time your kids spend glued to their tech devices can be difficult, but the tips included in this post could really help set some realistic boundaries.
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/how-to-set-real-world-limits-around-kids-and-tech/23snaps-child-tech-limits/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094279"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-39740094279" alt="23snaps; Child tech limits" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-Child-tech-limits.jpg" width="448" height="362" /></a></p>
Technology is an everyday part of a child’s life these days. It’s also something that is next to impossible to eliminate it, no matter how much a parent may want to. Kids as young as two and three are commonly using apps on smart phones and tablets, and by the time they enter school, computers are a regular part of how they learn. So how do you set limits around tech so your child can benefit from what it offers without being overwhelmed by it? Here are some tips that can help ... (to continue reading click <a href="http://www.nannyjobs.net/blog/how-to-set-real-world-limits-around-kids-and-tech/">here</a>)

				<title>What does a family photo sharing service need?</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/what-does-a-family-photo-sharing-service-need/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 22 May 2013 13:30:50 +0000</pubDate>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094296</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/what-does-a-family-photo-sharing-service-need/23snaps-photo-sharing-services-3/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094299"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094299" alt="23snaps; photo sharing services 3" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-photo-sharing-services-3-150x150.jpg" width="143" height="143" /></a><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/what-does-a-family-photo-sharing-service-need/23snaps-photo-sharing-services-5/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094300"><img class="wp-image-39740094300 alignleft" style="margin-left: 55px; margin-right: 55px;" alt="23snaps; photo sharing services 5" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-photo-sharing-services-5-150x150.jpg" width="143" height="143" /></a><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/what-does-a-family-photo-sharing-service-need/23snaps-photo-sharing-services-6/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094298"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094298" style="margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;" alt="23snaps; photo sharing services 6" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-photo-sharing-services-6-150x150.jpg" width="143" height="143" /></a>

&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/?attachment_id=39740094301"> </a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

What are the most important elements in a family photo sharing service? We believe the key features are privacy and security, ease of use, cross-platform sharing capabilities, storage space and appearance.

When you entrust your precious memories to a photo sharing service, you want to be sure that your images are safe. A lot of sites have customizable privacy settings that you can tailor to suit your individual needs, however as we've seen <a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/media/2009/jun/11/smith-family-photo-czech-advertisement" target="_blank">fairly regularly</a> in recent years, these are not always effective or clear. It's important to read and understand the terms and conditions of the photo sharing service you've chosen.

If not everyone in the family is completely tech-savvy, you'll want a service that provides great features for the tech-whiz while still being simple enough for the less technologically-inclined to use. Some photo sharing services may seem like a great fit for your family but could end up being too complicated for some family members.

The world is becoming more connected – but that doesn’t mean everyone has agreed on one social network or technology. What if you’re using one photo sharing service but you also want to share a couple of your favorite pictures with friends and co-workers on Facebook? Or what if you use an iPhone but your sister uses an Android phone and your parents are only comfortable on the web? A photo sharing service for your family and friends should allow you to connect with the right people in the right places.

Of course upload limits are pretty important when choosing a place to store your photos. There's not much point in setting up an account and inviting all of your family to connect with you if you can’t upload all your content. There are a few services out there, 23snaps included, that allow unlimited uploads for free. Others are unlimited for a small fee.

Finally, what does the service look like? If it's not remotely attractive and you don't enjoy looking at your photos – you’re not going to use it. Simple.

This seems to be a bit of a hot topic at the moment, after Flikr's revamp of their service. Although they now offer all users 1TB of space, some of their existing users are <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-22608122" target="_blank">unhappy about the change.</a> What do you think? What are the most important features in a family photo sharing service? What can services like Flickr, 23snaps and others do to make a better service for families?

With the huge choice of photo sharing services available today, it is always worth taking a little extra time to decide which is best for you (and if you're looking for a service that includes all of the properties featured above ... well, we'd recommend 23snaps!).

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Create your own watermark to help keep your photos safe online</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 30 May 2013 15:10:39 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094353</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Adding a watermark to your photos is much simpler than you might expect, and it could prevent someone from using your images without your consent. You can create a simple watermark that won't detract from the image you wish to share, but will make it plain that you hold the rights to that image.

<em><strong>                       Before                                                                            After</strong></em>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/23snaps-watermark-before/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094369"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-39740094369" alt="23snaps; Watermark - Before" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-Watermark-Before-225x300.jpg" width="225" height="300" /></a>            <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/23snaps-watermark-after/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094368"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-39740094368" alt="23snaps; Watermark - After" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/23snaps-Watermark-After-225x300.jpg" width="225" height="300" /></a>

&nbsp;

Below you'll find some easy, step-by-step instructions on how to create your own watermark. The software used in this example is Gimp, a photo editing programme that you can download for free <a href="http://www.gimp.org/downloads/">here</a>, however the process would be very similar when using most photoshop programmes.

&nbsp;

Open the icon/logo/text you wish to make into your watermark in your photoshop software.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-35-24/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094354"><img class=" wp-image-39740094354 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Watermark 1" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.35.24-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

Duplicate and arrange your watermark as you see fit to create your ideal watermark design.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-36-55/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094355"><img class=" wp-image-39740094355 alignnone" alt="Screen Shot 2013-05-30 at 14.36.55" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.36.55-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

Merge all of the separate layers that make up your watermark into one, to do this you need to right click on the top layer of those you wish to combine and select Merge Down.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-37-09/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094356"><img class=" wp-image-39740094356 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Watermark 3" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.37.09-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

Now you need to make your watermark white, so as not to detract from your image. Right click on your watermark design and from the drop down menu(s) select Colours&gt;Levels.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-37-31/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094357"><img class=" wp-image-39740094357 alignnone" alt="Screen Shot 2013-05-30 at 14.37.31" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.37.31-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

Drag the slider on the left edge of the "Output Level" bar as far to the right as it will go until your watermark has turned completely white.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-37-42/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094358"><img class=" wp-image-39740094358 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Watermark 4" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.37.42-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

To reduce the opacity of your watermark you need to locate the Opacity option at the top of your Layers Dock, this should be set to 100 by default.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-37-50/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094359"><img class=" wp-image-39740094359 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Watermark 5" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.37.50-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

Change the opacity level to 50. (The watermark only looks grey because of the black background. It will still be white in the end!)

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-38-18/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094360"><img class=" wp-image-39740094360 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Watermark 6" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.38.18-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

Finally, you need to delete your background layer in order to lay your new watermark over your photos.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-38-39/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094361"><img class=" wp-image-39740094361 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Watermark 7" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.38.39-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

This is what you will be left with, right now it doesn't look like much but ...

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-38-41/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094362"><img class=" wp-image-39740094362 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Watermark 8" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.38.41-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

&nbsp;

once it is layered over one of your photos, it looks like a very professional watermark.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-create-your-own-watermark-to-help-keep-your-photos-safe/screen-shot-2013-05-30-at-14-24-06/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094363"><img class=" wp-image-39740094363 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Watermark 9" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-Shot-2013-05-30-at-14.24.06-1024x640.png" width="512" height="320" /></a>

Export your image as a .jpeg file but REMEMBER to save your watermark layer (minus the actual photo) as a .png file to easily apply it to your photos later.]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Who owns the photos you post online?</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-who-owns-the-photos-you-post-online/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 04 Jun 2013 13:13:53 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094389</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-who-owns-the-photos-you-post-online/23snaps-who-owns-your-photos-once-you-post-them-online/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094392"><img class="wp-image-39740094392 aligncenter" alt="23snaps; Who owns your photos once you post them online?" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-Who-owns-your-photos-once-you-post-them-online-1024x875.jpg" width="410" height="350" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr">If you take a photo, you own it, right? That’s what you would expect, it was who you took the photo in the first place. However, once you post a photo to certain sharing sites you effectively give them permission to do whatever they like with your precious photo. This is why it’s imperative to fully understand the Terms &amp; Conditions of a site before you decide to upload your images.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The T&amp;Cs differ hugely from site to site. Although most concede to the fact that the photos you post are still owned solely by you, by uploading an image to their site you are giving them <em>license to use</em> it. This means you could still see your face <a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/media/2009/jun/11/smith-family-photo-czech-advertisement">smiling down from a billboard</a> without ever knowingly having consented to the use of your photo. The term <em>license to use</em> means that whilst you do still own the photo, the sharing site has the right to use it in its promotional activities, and it can transfer or sub-license that right to its partners. This license doesn’t work in reverse though, you have no right to use any of the images owned by the site … although it’s unlikely you’d ever want or need to.</p>
<p dir="ltr">There are other terms you should also be wary of, any of the following can technically allow the site to use your photos for their own gain. When a photo sharing service asks you to agree to permit them to use, copy, reproduce, process, adapt, modify, publish, transmit, display or distribute your photos, it’s probably not the best place to share precious family memories you would rather keep private.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The easiest way to ensure you’re comfortable posting your photos online for your friends and family to enjoy is to take a quick course in “legalese”. If you understand what these few phrases mean and make sure you look out for them, you should easily avoid giving away the rights to your photos.</p>
<em><strong>Use</strong></em>

There are no parameters on what the term Use could include, it basically concede various rights to the owners of the site.
<p dir="ltr"><em><strong>Adapt &amp;/or modify</strong></em></p>
<p dir="ltr">Again, these terms could cover a lot, for example cropping an image to show only part of your photo rather than the whole thing if it were used as part of a promotional campaign.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><em><strong>Display &amp;/or distribute</strong></em></p>
<p dir="ltr">These terms give the service permission to use your photos in promotional activities such as advertising campaigns, although it would be unlikely that your photo would wind up on a billboard.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong><em>Transferable &amp;/or sub-licensable</em></strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">This lets the service transfer the rights to your photos to any partner they may work with now or in the future – for example, an advertising partner.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong><em>Royalty-free</em></strong></p>
If any profit is made as a result of using your photo, it will be the site owners getting rich … not you.

&nbsp;

Whichever service you decide to use to share your photos, it's most likely you will still be the legal owner of the images you post, but be careful not to get tripped up by the terms of use that will allow them to use your photos, despite their apparent lack of ownership.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Guest Post; Tips for travelling with Children</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/guest-post-tips-for-travelling-with-children/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 06 Jun 2013 09:58:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094403</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<em>Today we have a first ever Guest Post, and we are very excited to share this fantastic piece from the lovely ladies over at <a href="http://www.myfamilymagazine.co.uk/">My Family Magazine</a>. </em>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/guest-post-tips-for-travelling-with-children/23snaps-my-family-magazine-1/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094416"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-39740094416" alt="23snaps; My Family Magazine 1" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-My-Family-Magazine-1-1024x457.jpg" width="640" height="285" /></a>

<i><b>Tips for Travelling with Children</b></i>
&nbsp;
<b>Summer is here, and your thoughts have probably turned to getting out and about with the </b><b>family to make the most of the longer, warmer days.</b>

All families are different, but when it comes down to it there are some basic requirements for a good family trip.
&nbsp;
<b>The pleasure is in the detail</b>

If you are travelling with another family, discuss what each person wants to do before you go and dedicate childcare responsibilities during travel. Establish how much time you would like to spend together and come to anagreement about the way you'll split the bills and arrange how to share day-to-day responsibilities.If this is your first trip with your children, plan for a slower pace than you might usually attempt. Be realistic about what you can cover with little ones in tow and if you are travelling with a small child, a pram or buggy can be useful even if your child is walking. It will provide a place for them to rest when covering a lot of ground or a makeshift bed when they are worn out.
&nbsp;
<b>Keeping Everyone Safe</b>

More than 900 million international journeys are undertaken every year. Global travel on this scale exposes many people to a range of health risks. Many of these risks can be minimized by precautions taken before, during and after travel. For information on health risks for travellers visit <a href="http://www.who.int/ith/en/"><b>www.who.int/ith/en</b>/</a> and for travel vaccinations visit

<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/Travel-immunisation">www.nhs.uk/conditions/Travel-immunisation</a>

Always use a car seat when travelling by car regardless of the regulations in your destination. A universal model is a good idea if you are using a variety of vehicles or hiring a car. For general guidelines and information about fitting child's car and booster seats, go to <a href="http://www.childcarseats.org.uk"><b>www.childcarseats.org.uk</b></a>
&nbsp;
<b>Childcare</b>

Look into supervised childcare, such as kids' clubs before you go. Find out what activities the children will be involved in, how many children are cared for and whether the children are grouped by age. Be prepared to check it out yourself when you arrive and make sure that all the necessary paperwork including CRB checks are in place. If anything seems amiss, be prepared to cancel your plans and start looking for alternatives.
&nbsp;
<b>Sun Safety</b>

Enjoy the sun safely, whether you're at home or abroad, use shade, clothing and at least SPF15 sunscreen to protect yourself.

Young skin is delicate and very easily damaged by the sun. All children, no matter whether they tan easily or not, should be protected from the sun.

Children with fair or red hair, pale eyes or freckles are at most risk. Keep babies under six months out of direct sunlight, especially around midday.
&nbsp;
<b>Tips for protecting children in the sun:</b>

<b>1 Set good habits for the future </b>–

teaching children safe sun habits while they are young sets a good pattern for later life.

<b>2 Remember you can burn in the UK </b>–

The Great British sun is quite capable of burning your child! Take extra care at home as well as abroad.

<b>3 Use shade </b>–

Keep babies in complete shade: under trees, umbrellas, canopies or indoors and use pram/ buggy shades.

<b>4 Cover them up </b>–

When outdoors, protect a baby’s skin with loose-fitting clothes, and a wide-brimmed hat that shades their face, neck and ears.

<b>5 Wear sunglasses </b>–

Buy good quality, wraparound sunglasses for children, as soon as they can wear them. Sunglasses don't have to be expensive brands.

<b>6 Find hats they like </b>–

Encourage children to wear hats with brims, especially if they are not wearing sunglasses. The wider the brim, the more skin will be shaded from the sun.

<b>7 Use sunscreen wisely </b>–

Use at least a factor 15 sunscreen and choose a ‘broadspectrum’ brand that protects against UVA rays – the more stars the better. Apply to areas that cannot be protected by clothing, such as the face, ears, feet and backs of hands. Choose sunscreens that are formulated for children and babies' skin. These products are less likely to contain alcohol or fragrances that might irritate the skin and cause allergic reactions.

<b>8 Apply sunscreen generously and regularly </b>–

Put some on before children go outdoors. Sunscreen can easily be washed, rubbed, or sweated off – so reapply often throughout the day.

For more information visit <a href="http://www.sunsmart.org.uk"><b>www.sunsmart.org.uk</b></a>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Geo-tagging and location indicators</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-geo-tagging-and-location-indicators/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 07 Jun 2013 09:03:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094421</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-geo-tagging-and-location-indicators/23snaps-geo-tagging-and-location-indicators-1-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094426"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-39740094426" alt="23snaps; Geo-tagging and location indicators 1" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-Geo-tagging-and-location-indicators-11-1024x504.jpg" width="640" height="315" /></a>

When sharing your photographs online it is always worth being aware of how much information you're giving out. If you're sharing the photos in the first place it's probably safe to assume that you want people to see what you're up to, but how wise is it to let those people know exactly where you are in real-time? This is what geo-tagging does. Geo-tagging is the process of adding geographical identification metadata to your media, including photographs and videos. This can be a nice touch if you're sharing photos in a private space as it allows those that you trust to see where you've been enjoying yourself. <strong>BUT</strong> if those photos are public, any stranger could theoretically figure out exactly where you are without much difficulty. Constantly posting pictures showing that you're away from home could also leave you're house and belongings vulnerable.

The same holds true when taking photos that include location indicators. Taking a photo of a street name or landmark is great for when you're looking back and reminiscing about the places you've visited, but is it wise to include the name of your own road or your child's school? This would make it incredibly simple for someone to track you or your family down should they be so inclined.

This doesn't mean you should refrain from taking these pictures, you just need to be confident about the security of the environment into which you post them. If you absolutely can't resist, you can blur out the distinguishing features. Take precautions and protect your family's safety by keeping photos that giveaway your location off of the more public sharing sites.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-geo-tagging-and-location-indicators/23snaps-geo-tagging-and-location-indicators-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094427"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740094427" alt="23snaps; Geo-tagging and location indicators 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-Geo-tagging-and-location-indicators-2.jpg" width="604" height="402" /></a>

If you'd like to take an extra step in keeping your location private, you can turn off the geo-tagging feature (at least, you can with 23snaps!). You can choose to either turn off the GPS on your phone altogether, which will automatically prevent the photo from being tagged with a location because it wouldn't be able to detect it's own position. If you don't want to lose the ability to use your phone's inbuilt GPS altogether you can usually go into the general settings and turn off the location services for individual apps. On an iOS device you would do this by clicking Settings&gt;Privacy&gt;Location Services and then manually turning off the permission for each app. Unfortunately Android devices don't currently offer this option, but there are various apps that give you this capability. One such app is <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.lbe.security.lite&amp;feature=search_result">LBE Privacy Guard</a>; this app allows you to protect your privacy by controlling the permission of each application to access your sensitive data (such as location services), however it does require that you <a href="http://smartphones.yoexpert.com/how-to-guides-7565/what-is-rooting-and-what-are-the-benefits-of-rooti-20478.html">root your phone</a> first. Another option is <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.james.SmartUninstaller&amp;hl=en">Android App Manager</a>, which again will let you individually switch off various permissions for each of your individual apps without rooting your device.

Digital photos have always included large amounts of meta-information, and smart phones and devices have taken this information and made a much better use of it. The problem is not necessarily that the images include this information, but what is done with it by the service you use to share your photos. As long as the geo-location information in not publicly displayed in a way that you were not expecting, you don't need to panic about the fact that the information exists in the file.

Our advice boils down to this: consider what information you want to make public, and who you'd want to be able to find you, before you post your photos publicly online.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>What sort of content is appropriate to share online?</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-what-sort-of-content-is-appropriate-to-share-online/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 14 Jun 2013 11:09:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094504</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-what-sort-of-content-is-appropriate-to-share-online/23snaps-what-content-is-appropeiate-to-post-online/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094527"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740094527" alt="23snaps; what content is appropeiate to post online" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-what-content-is-appropeiate-to-post-online.jpg" width="640" height="304" /></a>

There are no hard and fast rules as to what you should and should not post online, what each individual feels is appropriate may differ hugely to their friends and family. However there are a few loose guideline that we think could be universally agreed upon and could help reduce the unease some parents feel about sharing their photos online.

<em><strong><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-what-sort-of-content-is-appropriate-to-share-online/23snaps-donts/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094512"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094512" alt="23snaps; Don'ts" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-Donts.jpg" width="94" height="118" /></a>Don't</strong> </em>embarrass your children. Once a photo is posted online, there's no guarantee that it can ever be completely erased. Just because you think that exploding diaper photo you just took is super cute and funny, in 15 years time, they might not appreciate the world seeing them covered in poop. How would you feel if your parents broke out your baby photos around your friends, co-workers, or even complete strangers? Yeh, that's  exactly how your child is going to feel about <em>that</em> photo in a few years.

<em><strong><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-what-sort-of-content-is-appropriate-to-share-online/23snaps-dos/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094511"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094511" alt="23snaps; Do's" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-Dos.jpg" width="94" height="118" /></a>Do</strong> </em>show off every once in a while. Although constant bragging about how great your child is at this, or how quickly they learnt how to do that, could seem a little obnoxious, don't be afraid to post content depicting big milestones. Your excited that your little one took their first steps? You can be pretty sure your family will be excited too! Don't deprive them of the opportunity to enjoy the moment with you for fear of showing off.

<em><strong><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-what-sort-of-content-is-appropriate-to-share-online/23snaps-donts/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094512"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094512" alt="23snaps; Don'ts" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-Donts.jpg" width="94" height="118" /></a>Don't</strong></em><strong> </strong>share more than you mean to. If you're sharing photos on any public platform, never post images of your child unless they're fully clothed. We know, we know ... bath time photos are SO cute, but unless you're 100% sure of who can access your photos and the intentions they have in viewing them, it's just not worth the risk. Although we would like to point out that the risk of anyone actually using your photos in an unsavoury manner is actually incredibly small.

<em><strong><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-what-sort-of-content-is-appropriate-to-share-online/23snaps-dos/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094511"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094511" alt="23snaps; Do's" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-Dos.jpg" width="94" height="118" /></a>Do</strong></em> be aware of "valuable" photos. Uploading photos of your family frolicking around your brand new car, enjoying a tasty name brand snack or wearing an obviously branded item of clothing could lead to your photo becoming the new ad image for the brand that just so happened to feature in your photo. Posting pictures such as these seems almost like offering big brands the chance to use your photos.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-what-sort-of-content-is-appropriate-to-share-online/23snaps-white/" rel="attachment wp-att-39740094524"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740094524" alt="23snaps: white" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-white.jpg" width="94" height="118" /></a>The same goes for turning your photos into Memes (usually adding a humorous caption to a funny photo). If you really can't resist sharing it online in the hope that your friends find it funny, just be aware that they might not be able to resist sharing it either, with people you never intended to see it.

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>What should you do if you feel your online privacy has been violated?</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-what-should-you-do-if-you-feel-your-online-privacy-has-been-violated/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 17 Jun 2013 15:21:22 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740094531</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="size-large wp-image-39740094623 alignnone" alt="23snaps; Online privacy violation" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/23snaps-Online-privacy-violation-1024x475.png" width="640" height="296" />

It's the thing many parents fear most about posting photos online - somebody's gained access to your photos without your express permission. What should you do now? First things first, take a deep breath, it is very unlikely that any emotional or physical harm will come to you or your family because of this. Second, evaluate the situation; what exactly has happened? How bad is it really? Has somebody had the opportunity to view photos that you would rather they weren't privvy too? Or have your images been used on another site without your consent? If the issue is the former, then it's probably not the end of the world. We would recommend adjusting your privacy settings or maybe closing the account with whichever service you feel has failed to protect your privacy.

If someone has used your image without your knowledge or consent, then it's likely you'll feel more violated. To start with you should get in touch with whoever posted your photo. If you ask them nicely to remove it, it's probable that they will be accommodating. They may not have even realised they were doing anything wrong! If this doesn't work you can try reporting a violation of privacy to the site. If the individual involved won't take down the photo the owners of the site usually have the ability to intervene. As an extra precaution to prevent this from happening again in future, you could disconnect with anyone involved in the re-posting of your image, or if that seems too extreme, politely let them know that they've crossed a line.

If for any reason you have difficulty getting the photo taken down, remember, even though content lingers on the internet, as time passes it will become increasingly hard to find. On Facebook alone, over 300 million images are uploaded every day, before too long the photo will get lost in the sea of photos available online.

It is important to keep in mind that the internet is primarily a public resource, and there are many people out there that believe if they can see an image online, then they have the right to use it. If the thought of other people using your images makes you uncomfortable, make sure you're careful about the platform on which you choose to share your photos, some are definitely more secure than others.]]></content:encoded>
