	<item>
				<title>Google+ Photo Editing Tool – Creative adjustments</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-creative-adjustments/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 08 Oct 2013 10:17:06 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095747</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This post is the second part of our raving introduction to the Google+ Editing Tools, if you missed the first part you can pop back and read it <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-basic-adjustments/">here</a> ... go on, we'll wait.

All done? Great! Now that everyone is up to speed, we can move on to some of the more creative tools that Google+ provides. There are a number of different ways that you can alter your image, all of which can make your photo absolutely stunning.

If you haven't already done so you'll need to <strong>upload your photo</strong>(s) to Google+. Then you just need to open the photo you wish to work on, and select <em><strong>Edit</strong></em> from the menu bar at the top of the lightbox.

You now have 7 different elements to play with.

<strong>Black &amp; White</strong>

This one does exactly what it says on the tin! Use the Black &amp; White tool to change your photo into a beautifully monochromatic image, you also have the option to alter the brightness, contrast and grain. If you don't want to alter these yourself, you can choose from 6 preset filters.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095748" style="margin-left: 12px; margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png" width="90" height="134" /></a>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.33.34.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095749" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.33.34.png" width="90" /></a>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.33.47.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095750" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.33.47.png" width="90" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.34.00.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095751" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.34.00.png" width="90" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.36.00.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095752" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.36.00.png" width="90" height="136" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.36.12.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095753" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-15.36.12.png" width="90" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<strong>Centre focus </strong>

This tool will allow you to draw attention to the main subject of your photo by blurring and adjusting the brightness of the surrounding background. You can adjust the depth of the blur to the surrounding background as well as individually altering the brightness of both the subject and the background.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095748" style="margin-left: 12px; margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png" width="180" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.05.09.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095757" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.05.09.png" width="180" height="269" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.06.33.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095758" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.06.33-202x300.png" width="180" height="269" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<strong>Drama</strong>

Now you can add style with a custom effect specifically tailored to your photos, ranging from subtle textures to wildly artistic effects. You can adjust the tonality with the following options: Dark, Normal &amp; Light, you can also choose between a Smooth or Coarse Texture. Finally, use the sliders to perfect the Strength and Saturation of your image.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095748" style="margin-left: 12px; margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201-200x300.png" width="90" height="135" /></a><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095759" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.14.18-198x300.png" width="90" height="135" /> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.14.41.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095760" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.14.41-198x300.png" width="90" height="135" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.14.53.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095761" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.14.53-200x300.png" width="90" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.15.07.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095762" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.15.07-201x300.png" width="90" height="135" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.15.18.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095763" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.15.18-199x300.png" width="90" height="135" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<strong>Frames</strong>

Select from 23 different frames to add a stylised finish to your photos. (Also we'd like to point out that maybe Google+ are trying to hint at something with their choice of 23 frames ... you know? How they're perfect for photos uploaded to 23snaps!) You can also adjust the thickness of the frame on your image, to help your add a really personalised touch.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095748" style="margin-left: 12px; margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201-200x300.png" width="140" /></a><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.38.11.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095766" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.38.11-198x300.png" width="140" height="210" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.37.50.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095765" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.37.50-202x300.png" width="140" height="210" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.38.30.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095767" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.38.30-200x300.png" width="140" height="210" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<strong>Tilt-shift </strong>

This tool enable's you to simulate depth of field by creating a narrow in-focus area. You're given the ability to select either a circular field or a strip across your image which you can then use to draw focus. This tool gives you the option to alter the severity of the transition of the in-focus area to the blurred background.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095748" style="margin-left: 12px; margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201-200x300.png" width="250" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.56.06.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095768" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-16.56.06-201x300.png" width="250" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<strong>Vintage films </strong>

Apply any one of the preset filters to simulate a vintage colour film photo from the 50s, 60s or 70s. You can choose between any one of the 12 Styles, if you wish to edit your image further, you can then individually adjust the Brightness, Saturation, Style Strength and Vignette.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095748" style="margin-left: 12px; margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201-200x300.png" width="140" height="210" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.04.00.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095771" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.04.00-200x300.png" width="140" height="210" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.04.12.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095772" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.04.12-200x300.png" width="140" height="210" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.04.35.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095773" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.04.35-198x300.png" width="140" height="210" /></a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<strong>Retrolux</strong>

Finally, make your photos look truly retro with light leaks, scratches, film styles and more. There are SO MANY options here, that the only way you can even begin to understand is to <a href="https://plus.google.com/photos">go an get stuck in</a>!

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095748" style="margin-left: 12px; margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-03-at-10.17.201-200x300.png" width="105" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.21.55.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095774" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.21.55-201x300.png" width="105" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.22.16.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095775" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.22.16-201x300.png" width="105" height="157" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.22.38.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095776" style="margin-right: 12px;" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.22.38-197x300.png" width="105" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.22.58.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-39740095777" alt="23snaps; Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-07-at-17.22.58-200x300.png" width="105" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Google+ Photo Editing Tool, Picassa &amp; 23snaps</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-picassa-23snaps/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 10 Oct 2013 08:35:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095793</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[We've already told you all about how to make the most of the<strong> brilliant new photo editing tools from Google+</strong>. You have the ability to make <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-basic-adjustments/">basic adjustments</a> to your photo as well as getting really <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-creative-adjustments/">creative</a>, but now we want to tell you about the bit that excites us the most ... <strong>sharing these photos on <a href="http://23snaps.com?utm_source=social&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=google%2B">23snaps</a>!</strong> Now that you've taken the time to create these stunning images, how could you resist sharing them with your family and friends via your <a href="http://23snaps.com?utm_source=social&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=google%2B">beautifully presented digital journal</a>.

Did you know that it is really easy to <strong>sync Picassa with Google+</strong>? If you use Picassa to manage to your digital photos, all you have to do is click one button and your photos will be synced to Google+, where you can edit to your hearts content. From there, it's so easy to upload them to 23snaps. Just by selecting Picassa from the list options when uploading photos to your 23snaps account, you will be able to choose any, or <em>all</em>, of the images you have edited on Google+ and share them with your close friends and family.

Although we use Picassa here at 23snaps HQ, we're by no means experts, so if you have yet to use Picassa we would recommend you pop over to their <a href="https://support.google.com/picasa/?hl=en-GB">help desk</a> for help getting started.

Now that you're all set up with Picassa, we can talk you through just how easy it is to get your original photos from your computer to 23snaps, without missing out on the Google+ editing tools. First things first, you need to get your photos from Picassa to Google+, and to do this all you have to do is <strong>open up Picassa and click the <em>Sync to Web</em></strong> button beside your chosen folder.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Google+-Photo-Editing-1.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095795" alt="Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Google+-Photo-Editing-1.png" width="500" /></a>

All of the photos that you sync to Google+ in this way will <strong>automatically be set to private</strong>, so you don't need to worry about inadvertently sharing your precious baby photos with the entire world.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-09-at-12.21.47.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-39740095796" alt="Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-09-at-12.21.47-300x168.png" width="300" height="168" /></a>

Now that your album has been uploaded to your Google+ profile, you can get started with the editing tools. As we've already been over that in <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-basic-adjustments/">part 1</a> and <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-creative-adjustments/">part 2</a> of this post, we will move straight on to the next step ... posting your edited photos to 23snaps!

We're sure you already know how to <strong>upload photos to 23snaps</strong>, but just in case ...

Click on the <em>Newsfeed</em> tab at the top of the page (this is the homescreen so you may already be there), then hit the orange <em><strong>+</strong> Post </em>button in the top right of the screen and choose the <em>Photo </em>option.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Google+-Photo-Editing-2.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095797" alt="Google+ Photo Editing " src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Google+-Photo-Editing-2-1024x546.png" width="500" /></a>

Click <em>Select Files</em>  which will give you the following options to choose from:

- My Computer

- Flikr

- Facebook

- Instagram

- Dropbox

- Picassa

Obviously <em>Picassa</em> is the option you're going to want to choose here. If this is the first time you're using Picassa with 23snaps, you will have to authorise access, just follow the steps that appear on the screen.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-09-at-15.09.52.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095798" alt="Google+ Photo Editing" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-09-at-15.09.52.png" width="400" /></a>

Here you will find all of those <strong>beautiful images you created in Google+</strong>, just select the one(s) you want to share on 23snaps and click <em>Upload</em>. There is a limit of 15 photos per upload batch, so if you want to share more the 15 photos that you have edited on Google+, you will just need to repeat the process.

You can then add a description to the photo(s), tag your child and decide when on the timeline it should appear. Finally click on the <em>Submit Photos</em> button to upload your post.

<strong>Ta da! Beautifully edited photos in your 23snaps feed for all of your friends and family to enjoy.</strong>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-09-at-16.11.21.png"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-39740095799" alt="Screen Shot 2013-10-09 at 16.11.21" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-09-at-16.11.21-1024x545.png" width="640" height="340" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps Tip of the Week - Share photos to 23snaps from your Android&#039;s device Gallery</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-tip-of-the-week-share-photos-to-23snaps-from-your-androids-device-gallery/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 11 Oct 2013 11:00:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095809</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Sometimes when you're looking back through photos that you've taken on your device, you might come across one that you've forgotten to share to 23snaps. Well it's so easy to rectify that! Rather than having to exit your Gallery and open 23snaps, you can upload it straight to your child's timeline from right where you are!

All you have to do is open the Image Gallery on your device and locate the image you wish to post (if you haven't already done so!). Now you'll need to tap the <em>Share </em>icon <img src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/ymyrpdedtvefyuz/?name=687474703a2f2f7777772e676f6f676c652e636f6d2f68656c702f68632f696d616765732f616e64726f69642f616e64726f69645f75675f34302f69635f6d656e755f73686172655f686f6c6f5f6c696768742e706e67.png" alt="687474703a2f2f7777772e676f6f676c652e636f6d2f68656c702f68632f696d616765732f616e64726f69642f616e64726f69645f75675f34302f69635f6d656e755f73686172655f686f6c6f5f6c696768742e706e67.png" width="15" height="14" /> at the top of the screen.

<img src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/scgimcjx4hwgfyb/?name=Share+from+Android+Gallery+1.jpg" alt="Share_from_Android_Gallery_1.jpg" width="200" />

From the options you're offered, select the <em>23snaps </em>icon.

<img title="Image: /attachments/token/kwni3xepmcxptds/?name=Share+from+Android+Gallery+2.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/kwni3xepmcxptds/?name=Share+from+Android+Gallery+2.jpg" alt="Share_from_Android_Gallery_2.jpg" width="200" />

You will immediately be taken to the Photo Editor, where you can filter, vignettes and make any alterations you wish. Once you're happy with the image, click <em>Done. </em>

<img src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/kync0u3dys0hvtm/?name=Share+from+Android+Gallery+3.jpg" alt="Share_from_Android_Gallery_3.jpg" width="200" />

You can now add a description, tag your child and decide when on the timeline the image should appear. Then tap the orange <em>Publish</em> button in the top right hand corner and your photo will be uploaded to 23snaps.

<img title="Image: /attachments/token/tmdztmcnedfssta/?name=Share+from+Android+Gallery+4.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/tmdztmcnedfssta/?name=Share+from+Android+Gallery+4.jpg" alt="Share_from_Android_Gallery_4.jpg" width="200" />

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Concerns about online safety &amp; cyber-bullying.</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/concerns-about-online-safety-cyber-bullying/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 04 Nov 2013 12:00:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095224</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Cyberbulling.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095910" alt="Cyberbulling" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Cyberbulling.jpg" width="700" height="394" /></a>

Ahead of anti-bullying week in November a new survey has raised concerns about children and young people’s safety online. The poll, carried out by <a title="Anti-bullying Alliance" href="http://www.anti-bullyingalliance.org.uk/">Anti-Bullying Alliance</a>, questioned 2,200 parents, children and teachers in England and found that 55% of children were sadly resigned to the fact that cyber-bullying was normal practice and a part of everyday life now, a point to which a staggering 60% of parents agreed. Cyber-bullying is an electronic form of communication that uses cyber-technology or digital media to hurt, threaten, embarrass, annoy, blackmail or otherwise target another individual.

These findings highlight a real need for more information, for both parents and children, about how to protect against and deal with online bullying. The majority (67%) of children claimed that should they fall victim to cyber bullying, they would inform their parents, however 40% of parents admitted that they wouldn't know how deal with the issue. Steps such as setting up filters on mobile phones and computers are concepts that many parents don't understand. Having grown up in a far less digital age, it is not uncommon to see the parents turning to their children for their online education, but in situations concerning the children's well-being, it is imperative that parents are equipped with the appropriate tools.

Unfortunately it seems that teachers and parents are not always able to provide the advice and support young people need. In order to help rectify this, we wanted to provide you with some of the best resources to answer some of the more frequently asked questions:

<a href="http://quib.ly/qu/how-can-i-start-a-conversation-with-my-child-to-find-out-if-theyre-being-cyberbullied">How can I tell if my child is being bullied online?</a> And <a href="http://quib.ly/qu/what-can-i-do-if-my-child-is-being-cyberbullied">if they are, what to I do?</a>

<a href="http://quib.ly/qu/what-should-a-parent-be-in-the-look-out-for-to-know-whether-his-child-is-exhibiting-bullying-behaviour-online">Is my child being a cyber-bully?</a>

<a href="http://quib.ly/qu/can-you-set-parental-controls-on-the-ipad">Can you set parental controls on iPhones and iPads?</a>

<a href="http://quib.ly/qu/what-is-snapchat">What is Snapchat?</a>

<a href="http://quib.ly/qu/what-is-askfm-and-why-should-i-care">What is Ask.fm?</a> And <a href="http://quib.ly/qu/is-askfm-ok-for-teens-my-take-is-httptinyurlcomnzcesb6">is it OK for teens?</a>

<em>(Answers provided by <a href="http://quib.ly/">Quib.ly</a> and their registered experts)</em>

There is a definite fear about the likelihood of children being involved in online bullying, which makes it all the more concerning that the survey figures revealed that 43% of teachers said their school did not currently teach anything about cyber-bullying and online safety. This reflects the growing calls for online safety to be taught in more schools, with 69% of teachers and 40% of young people advocating that the topic should be included in the national curriculum.

Luke Roberts, National Co-ordinator of the Anti-Bullying Alliance said “The solution is better education, not only in the classroom, but better training for teachers and support for parents.”

It's important that adults and children alike educate themselves about this issue in order to try an stop it from happening. People feel far more comfortable about picking on others from the perceived safety of their keyboard, they may say things online that they would otherwise never have found acceptable to say in person. Behaviour such as this may not be deliberately vindictive, but when children are involved it can have a profound affect on both the bully and the bullied. As a parent it is so important that you monitor your child's social media account as they provide an easy platform for this type of behaviour. Although we wouldn't advocate invading your child's privacy, it is always worth keeping an eye on what they, and their friends, post online.]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>39740095224</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2013-11-04 12:00:28</wp:post_date>

	<item>
				<title>How does Twitter work?</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/how-does-twitter-work/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Oct 2013 11:30:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095816</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr">Twitter is one of the biggest social networks around today. It allows users to post <strong>140 character updates</strong> about anything they feel is interesting or useful to their followers. A Twitter follower is anyone who has chosen to subscribe to your tweets</p>
<p dir="ltr">It is up to each individual Twitter user to decide who they want to follow, this allows them to dictate which tweets will appear on their homepage.</p>
<p dir="ltr">When you use Twitter you will see 4 different feeds within your account, these are Home, @Connect feed, #Discover and Me.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- <strong>Home</strong> is the homepage, or “Newsfeed”, as mentioned above</p>
<p dir="ltr">- <strong>@Connect</strong> will show any tweets that interact with you in any way</p>
<p dir="ltr">- <strong>#Discover</strong> allows you to find other interesting people and information</p>
<p dir="ltr">- <strong>Me</strong> is the feed that contains all of your own tweets and interactions with other Twitter users</p>
&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr"><em><strong>Home, Following and Followers</strong></em></p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Twitter-Followers-Ecard.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095827" alt="Twitter How To 6" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Twitter-Followers-Ecard.png" width="374" height="263" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr">The main page that Twitter users are generally interested in is their homepage, once you’ve decided to follow some other users, this is where you will see their tweets. It works like a <strong>constantly updating Newsfeed</strong> You will not see anything tweeted by anybody that you are not currently following (unless it’s a retweet, but we’ll get to that a bit later).</p>
<p dir="ltr">By following someone you are essentially subscribing to their tweets. You will now be able to see anything they post. This means that anyone that has followed you is subscribing to your tweets and can see anything you post.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><em><strong>@Messages and @Mentions</strong></em></p>
<p dir="ltr">In order to<strong> interact with another Twitter user</strong>, you will need to make use of the @message/@mention. This is when a users twitter handle is included in another user’s tweet. This can be used in various ways; to write to a specific person you would begin your tweet with their handle:</p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/23Snaps"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095818" alt="23snaps: Twitter How To 1" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-16-at-11.53.51.png" width="640" height="284" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr">This tweet would be referred to as an <strong>@message</strong> and would appear in our <strong>@Connect feed</strong> as it is a tweet that interacts with us, but it would not appear on our Homepage. This tweet would only appear on our followers’ homepages if they also followed both the original tweeter and us. A follower must follow both parties involved in an @message in order to see the tweet in their homepage.</p>
&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr">If that Twitter user wanted to bring a tweet to our attention, but also wanted all of their followers to see it, regardless of whether they also followed us, they <strong>shouldn’t start the tweet with our handle</strong>, but place it anywhere else within the text:</p>
<a href="https://twitter.com/23Snaps"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095819" alt="23snaps: Twitter How To 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-16-at-11.54.42.png" width="644" height="280" /></a>

This is an <strong>@mention </strong>and again it would appear in our <strong>@Connect</strong> feed because someone is still interacting with us, however if we followed the original tweeter this would also appear in our Homepage as it is not considered an @message.

&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr">Another great way to do this, if you want to seem like you’re talking to someone in particular, but in a public way, you can pop a <strong>period (.) before their twitter handle</strong> at the beginning of the message. This stops the tweet from being an @message and makes it an @mention:</p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/23Snaps"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095820" alt="23snaps: Twitter How To 3" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-16-at-11.55.28.png" width="644" height="254" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr">Clever, huh?</p>
&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr">Finally, If you use an @mention in an @message, it is <strong>only the first person mentioned and the tweeter</strong> that will determine whose homepage it will appear in:</p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/23Snaps"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095821" alt="23snaps: Twitter How To 4" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-16-at-11.56.16.png" width="638" height="281" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr">In this example, only the people that follow both <a href="https://twitter.com/23Snaps">@23snaps</a> and @tweeter will be able to see this in their homepage. @Facebook will also see this tweet in their @Connect feed as they were @mentioned, but it would not appear in their followers feeds.</p>
&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr"><em><strong>DMs, Retweeting and Hashtags</strong></em></p>
<p dir="ltr">A DM (or Direct Message) is a <strong>private tweet from one user to another</strong>. This will not appear in any of the 4 feeds in either parties account, or in any of their followers’ homepages. It is only possible to send a DM to one of your followers, however if you do not follow them too, they will be unable to DM you back. Direct messages are the only private way to converse on Twitter, you can think of DMs as really short emails. They are unsearchable on Twitter.</p>
&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr">A retweet is pretty self-explanatory. This is when somebody re-tweets (re-posts) something that another user has already posted. This will appear like so:</p>
<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/23Snaps"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095826" alt="Twitter How To 5" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Twitter-Retweet-eg.png" width="640" height="265" /></a></p>
<p dir="ltr">Note that the tweet is <strong>still credited to the original tweeter</strong>, but by retweeting it, it is then re-shared by a third party (in this case @23snaps) who wanted their followers to see it.</p>
&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr">Now, on to hashtags. In order to categorise your tweet or join in a specific conversation you can use a hashtag (#). <strong>The hashtag symbol is used before a relevant keyword or phrase in a tweet to categorise those tweets</strong> and help them show more easily in Twitter search.</p>
<p dir="ltr">If someone begins a conversation and they want multiple tweeters to join in, they could use a hashtag (eg. #chat) to allow anybody to find the tweets that contribute to that conversation. By using the hashtag #chat, your tweet would then appear in the conversation feed. Clicking on a hashtagged word in any message shows you all other Tweets marked with that keyword.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Hashtags can occur anywhere in the Tweet, at the beginning, middle, or end. Hashtagged words that become very popular are often Trending Topics.</p>
&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr">So … that just about covers all of the Twitter basics. It seems a little complicated when you first get started, but it really is pretty simple. Just in case you’re not quite following (excuse the pun!) here is a <strong>quick recap</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">- <strong>Follow</strong> someone to see their tweets.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Your tweets are <strong>seen by all of your followers</strong> in their homepage.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- To <strong>talk to someone directly</strong> (but not privately) @message them.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- To <strong>talk to someone privately</strong>, DM them.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- To talk about someone, but not necessarily too them, <strong>@mention</strong> them.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- To <strong>share someone else’s tweet</strong> with your followers, retweet it.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- To join in a conversation or add information to <strong>a particular topic</strong>, use a hashtag.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- To see <strong>who’s been talking to, or about, you</strong>, check your @Connections feed.</p>
<p dir="ltr">- To<strong> find fun new people to follow</strong>, or topics to engage with, use the #Discover feed.</p>
&nbsp;
<p dir="ltr">That pretty much sums it up. We hope you enjoy using your newfound Twitter knowledge, and don’t forget to follow <a href="https://twitter.com/23Snaps">@23snaps</a>!</p>
&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps Tip of the Week: Autopost from Instagram to 23snaps</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-tip-of-the-week-autopost-from-instagram-to-23snaps/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 18 Oct 2013 11:00:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095834</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Did you know that you can automatically post to 23snaps from your Instagram account just by adding <a href="http://statigr.am/tag/23snaps">#23snaps</a> in your Instagram photo description?! That's so cool right? Here's how you do it ...

<em><strong>Connecting with Instagram</strong></em>

To <strong>connect your 23snaps account with your Instagram account</strong> all you need to do is log in to your account on the <a href="http://23snaps.com/">23snaps website</a>. Then click on <em>"Your Name" </em>in the menu bar at the top of the screen and select <em>Social</em> from the dropdown menu. Now you need to click on the green <em>Connect with Instagram</em> button which will prompt you to log into your Instagram account using an existing name and password*. To confirm, click <em>Authorize</em> to complete the connection process.

<img class="alignleft" title="Image: /attachments/token/rctsmkleuil12ck/?name=Connect+to+Instagram.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/rctsmkleuil12ck/?name=Connect+to+Instagram.jpg" alt="Connect_to_Instagram.jpg" width="400" height="190" />     <img title="Image: /attachments/token/nxj49ofuendg1uy/?name=Connect+to+Instagram+2.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/nxj49ofuendg1uy/?name=Connect+to+Instagram+2.jpg" alt="Connect_to_Instagram_2.jpg" width="400" />

<img class="alignleft" title="Image: /attachments/token/dgiytnr7f7lnux9/?name=Connect+to+Instagram+3.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/dgiytnr7f7lnux9/?name=Connect+to+Instagram+3.jpg" alt="Connect_to_Instagram_3.jpg" width="400" height="190" />     <img src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/srotxgw1nb8rcyb/?name=Connect+to+Instagram+4.jpg" alt="Connect_to_Instagram_4.jpg" width="400" />

<em>*NB: if you don't already have an Instagram account you will need to set one up before attempting to connect.</em>

&nbsp;

<em><strong>Posting to 23snaps from Instagram</strong></em>

To include a photo that you post to Instagram to your 23snaps timeline all you have to do is <strong>use the hashtag #23snaps</strong>. When you share the image to your Instagram feed it will simultaneously be uploaded to your 23snaps account.

<img title="Image: /attachments/token/wpaypsu6w3zwftu/?name=imstagram2.png" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/wpaypsu6w3zwftu/?name=imstagram2.png" alt="imstagram2.png" />

&nbsp;

<em><strong>Tagging a child in 23snaps when posting from Instagram</strong></em>

When you post a photo to 23snaps from Instagram <strong>you still have the ability to tag your child</strong> in the 23snaps version of the image to ensure in is included in their 23snaps timeline. To do this you have 2 options, you can either use hashtag"child's name" (eg. #lilly), which will automatically tag the child by that name.

However, as your privacy is one of our biggest priorities, we are aware that you may wish to <strong>keep the name of your child private from your Instagram followers</strong>. This is why we have enabled the option to<strong> "nickname" your children</strong> when using a hashtag to tag them in 23snaps. To configure your child(ren)'s nicknames just head over to your Social Settings on 23snaps (click on <em>"Your Name" </em>in the menu bar at the top of the screen and select <em>Social</em> from the dropdown menu) and scroll down to the bottom of the page. Here you are given the option to add the new nicknames for your child(ren) that will be recognised when used on Instagram and ensure the correct tag is applied in 23snaps. Just make sure to click <em>Save</em> when you're done.

<img title="Image: /attachments/token/bymwltkwbnwbxup/?name=Unique+tagging+hashtags.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/bymwltkwbnwbxup/?name=Unique+tagging+hashtags.jpg" alt="Unique_tagging_hashtags.jpg" width="700" />

&nbsp;

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps Tip of the Week: Building a Multi-Family Photobook</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-tip-of-the-week-building-a-multi-family-photobook/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 25 Oct 2013 11:30:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095852</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[As it's coming up to Christmas (I know, I know it's still only October ... but it's time to start getting organised!), we wanted to show you just <strong>how perfect a 23snaps photobook is as a gift for any member of the family</strong>. Did you know that you can even build  a book made up of photos shared by more than one family? So, let's say you're looking for a gift for Grandma, and your children and all of your  nieces and nephews have their own 23snaps timelines, you can build one beautiful photobook containing <strong><em>ALL</em> of the children's photos</strong>. The only requirement? That you be connected to the parents of all the children you want to feature.

Let us show you how ...

This guide will detail how to build your book on the <a href="http://23snaps.com"><strong>23snaps website</strong></a>, but it is also possible to order prints and photobooks from our iOS app, if you want any help on how to place your order using this platform, just click <a href="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/200264788-23snaps-Printing-How-To"><em><strong>here</strong></em></a>.

First, you will need to log into your 23snaps account via the 23snaps website, then click on the <em><strong>Prints &amp; Books</strong></em> option in the menu bar at the top of the screen.

Select the option to <strong><em>Order Books</em></strong>.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-39740095856 alignnone" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-1-1024x599.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 1" width="640" height="374" /></a>

To create your order; click on the green <strong><em>Add Photos to Order</em></strong> button.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-2.jpg"><img class="wp-image-39740095857 alignnone" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-2.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 2" width="640" height="374" /></a>

Now you can start selecting the photos you want to include in your photobook, first decide whether you want to start with your own photos or those that have been shared with you by your friends and family. Your <strong>photos will all be arranged in chronological</strong> order in your book, so it doesn't matter which family's photos you choose to start with.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-3.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095858" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-3.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 3" width="640" /></a>

Once you have selected the images you wish to use from this users account, click <strong><em>Add Selected Photos</em></strong> in the bottom right corner of the screen.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-4.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095859" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-4.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 4" width="640" /></a>

Now, on to the next family members photos. Simply scroll to the bottom of the page and click the <strong><em>Add Photos to Order</em></strong> button again.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-5.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095860" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-5.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 5" width="640" /></a>

If you started with your own photos and are now moving on to a connection's photos, this is what you will see. You simply need to <strong>click on the family whose photos you want to add</strong> next.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-6.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095861" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-6.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 6" width="640" /></a>

When you've selected the images you wish to use from this users account, click <strong><em>Add Selected Photos</em></strong> again. You can repeat these steps until you have added all of the photos you want to include in your photobook. Remember you need at least a <strong>minimum of 24 photos</strong> in order to be able to place your order.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-4.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-39740095859" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-4-1024x596.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 4" width="640" height="372" /></a>

You can<strong> select which image you would like to use as your cover</strong> photo by hovering the curser over the selected photo until the option to  <em>Make Cover</em> appears, simply click on this button to make your selection. You can now view a digital preview of your photobook by clicking on <em>Preview Book i</em>n the top right corner of the screen.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-7.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095862" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-7.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 7" width="640" /></a>

You can scroll through a digital version of your photobook, to <strong>make sure everything looks perfect</strong>. If you are happy with your order, click <em>Place Order.</em>

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-8.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095863" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Book-8.jpg" alt="23snaps Photo Book 8" width="640" /></a>

Now you will need to enter your shipping address and credit card details, you are also given the opportunity to enter a discount code if you are lucky enough to have one! Finally click <em>Place Order</em> to complete the order process. Your photobook(s) will then be processed as quickly as possible and sent to your chosen shipping address. It <strong>can take up to 3 weeks from the date your order is placed for your photobook to arrive</strong>, so if you plan to give yours as a gift, please make sure you place your order in plenty of time.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps Digital Photo Frames!</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-digital-photo-frames/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 03 Nov 2013 12:00:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095871</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<b>Only 1 in 3 grandparents see family photos shared online, so 23snaps are bringing real-time photo sharing for families to digital photo frames.</b>

Almost two thirds (<b>64%</b>) of UK grandparents say they don’t use the social networks and websites where family photos are shared. This <b>isolated generation</b> miss out on family moments shared on sites like Instagram or Flickr. Fewer than 1 in 10 (<b>9.8%</b>) grandparents feel comfortable using these sites, according to our study*. And even though half (<b>53%</b>) of UK grandparents are on Facebook, only one in three (<b>36%</b>) say they are connected in all of the places family photos are shared online.<i> </i>

Today we're announcing a new way for families to share photos and memories using a surprisingly traditional device. We're just so pleased with the success of our photo print service, we wanted to offer families the option to buy d<strong>igital frames that connect over Wi-Fi to 23snaps, and display the latest photos.</strong>

<a href="http://shop.23snaps.com/products/23snaps-photo-frame"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095873" alt="23snaps Digital Photo Frame" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-frame-2-1024x762.png" width="500" height="372" /></a>

The frames, provided in partnership with manufacturer Pix-Star, provide all generations in a family with a simple and stylish way to enjoy photos of the children they love. The <strong>10.4” digital frames are Wi-Fi enabled and arrive ready to connect to existing 23snaps accounts</strong>.

It has always been a priority to make 23snaps accessible to family members who might miss out on cherished family moments that are now shared primarily online. Our partnership with Pix-Star and our <strong>new digital photo frames can sit on a mantel piece or kitchen table, showcasing the latest family photos</strong> without any additional effort.

The 23snaps frame from Pix-Star makes the perfect Christmas gift for family members and close friends. The frames are priced at $189 (£149) and are available in the UK &amp; Ireland, USA, Canada, Japan, France and Germany.

<a href="http://shop.23snaps.com/products/23snaps-photo-frame"><strong>Purchase you're digital photo frame now!</strong></a>

&nbsp;

<a href="http://shop.23snaps.com/products/23snaps-photo-frame"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095874" alt="23snaps Digital Photo Frame" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/picture-frame-3-1024x769.png" width="325" height="244" /></a> <a href="http://shop.23snaps.com/products/23snaps-photo-frame"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095872" alt="23snaps Digital Photo Frame" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-frame-1.png" width="275" height="294" /></a>

<em>*Of UK grandparents aged 40+ run by OnePoll for 23snaps</em>]]></content:encoded>

				<title>Halloween Photography Round-up</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/halloween-photography-round-up/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 29 Oct 2013 12:15:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095885</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[In order to help inspire you to take some awesome Halloween photos we've scoured the internet and rounded up our favourite Halloween photographs from some incredibly talented bloggers. We'd love to hear which ones inspired you and whether you'll give them a try.

<a href="http://www.iheartfaces.com/2012/10/creating-ghostly-portraits-in-photoshop/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095889" alt="23snaps; iHeartFaces" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/iHeartFaces.jpg" width="399" height="621" /></a>
We've been raving about this incredible ghostly portrait tutorial from Wendy VonSosen at <a href="http://iheartfaces.com" target="_blank">iHeartFaces.com</a> all week. She makes creating a hauntingly beautiful image look so easy!

&nbsp;

<a href="http://www.babymakingmachine.com/2012/11/18-weeks-pregnant-and-loving-all-this-candy.html"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095886" alt="23snaps; Baby Making Machine" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Baby-Making-Machine.jpg" width="640" /></a>
Jennifer, at <a href="http://www.babymakingmachine.com" target="_blank">Baby Making Machine</a>, wanted to capture the light from the doorway spilling over her daughter's face whilst she was trick-or-treating. Unfortunately all of the porches had bright lights, but we don't think it detracts from the beauty of the photo at all.

&nbsp;

<a href="http://www.helenjohnphotographyblog.com/2012/11/happy-halloween-from-my-pumpkin-potomac.html"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095888" alt="23snaps; Helen John Photography" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Helen-John-Photography-Blog.jpg" width="640" height="427" /></a>
Look at how amazing this impromptu photo shoot turned out when Helen at <a href="http://www.helenjohnphotographyblog.com">helenjohnphotography.com</a> grabbed her littlest one and just started snapping. It just goes to show how brilliant photos don't necessarily require a lot of preparation.

&nbsp;

<a href="http://blog.thecelebrationshoppe.com/2011/09/08/introducing-trick-or-treat/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-39740095891" alt="23snaps; The Celebration Shop" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/the-celebration-shop.jpg" width="615" height="519" /></a>
We love the incorporation of these cute props from Kim Byers at <a href="http://blog.thecelebrationshoppe.com">The Celebration Shoppe</a>. Halloween doesn't have to be all about the trick, the treat is just as good, and all of these lovely bright colours and cute faces make this photo a real treat!

&nbsp;

<a href="http://www.erinwallis.com/blog/2008/11/happy-halloween/"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095887" style="border: 1px solid black;" alt="23snaps; Erin Wallis" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Erin-Wallis.jpg" width="600" height="480" /></a>
Sometimes all you need is a costume and a cute face to create an incredible Halloween photo. Erin at <a href="http://www.erinwallis.com/blog/">erinwallisphotography.com</a> just took some quick shots on their way out trick-or-treating, and it's still resulted in one of our favorite shots.

&nbsp;

<a href="http://www.lolarosephotographyblog.com/?p=890"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095890" alt="23snaps; Lola Rose Photography Blog" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Lola-Rose-Photography-Blog.jpg" width="580" /></a>
By using a center focus to draw attention to the adorably cheeky witch, Kelly at <a href="http://www.lolarosephotographyblog.com">Lola Rose Photography</a> has created an instant atmosphere in this photo. We love that it's set outside in the daylight too, not all Halloween photos need to be taken at night.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps Tip of the Week: Disabling Location Indicators</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-tip-of-the-week-disabling-location-indicators/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2013 12:00:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095905</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[It hasn't been long since the social media world experienced a wave of fear about the geo-tagging that occurs in a digital photo’s metadata when taken on a smartphone, and whether it could risk your privacy. However, there is absolutely no reason to worry, it is so easy to control the exposure of this information, you just need to know how. This weeks Tip of the Week will explain exactly how to do this on both the <a href="http://23snaps.com?utm_source=social&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=TOTW">23snaps</a> iOS and Android apps.

<strong>iPhone, iPod and iPad</strong>

Apple very kindly allow you to turn the GPS off for individual apps on their devices, to prevent your location being posted in 23snaps all you need to do is tap <em><strong>Settings</strong></em>, then scroll down to <em><strong>Privacy</strong></em> and select <em><strong>Location Services</strong></em>. Finally, make sure the slider next to <em><strong>23snaps is switched to off</strong></em>. You're all done!

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-1_iphone_black_portrait1.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-39740095948" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-1_iphone_black_portrait1-149x300.png" alt="photo 1" width="149" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-2_iphone_black_portrait1.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-39740095949" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-2_iphone_black_portrait1-144x300.png" alt="photo 2" width="144" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-3_iphone_black_portrait1.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-39740095950" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-3_iphone_black_portrait1-143x300.png" alt="photo 3" width="143" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-4_iphone_black_portrait1.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-39740095951" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-4_iphone_black_portrait1-145x300.png" alt="photo 4" width="145" height="300" /></a>

&nbsp;

<strong>Android</strong>

Unfortunately, Android don't offer the option to switch off your GPS for individual apps, and we understand that you may not want to turn your GPS off completely if you use your device for maps and directions. However there is a very quick process that you can do each time you post, just to stop you location appearing for that moment.

When your about to upload some new content to 23snaps, before you start simply<em><strong> drag the status bar down</strong></em> to open your connection options. If your GPS is on the icon will appear lit up, simply <em><strong>tap it to disable the GPS</strong></em> for your device. Now you can post to 23snaps safe in the knowledge that your location will not be disclosed. In order to switch your GPS back on when your done, <em><strong>simply repeat the process</strong></em>.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-1-portrait.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095952" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-1-portrait-522x1024.png" alt="photo 1" width="210" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-2-portrait.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095953" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-2-portrait-541x1024.png" alt="photo 2" width="210" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-3-portrait.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095954" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-3-portrait-533x1024.png" alt="photo 3" width="210" /></a>

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

				<title>Add Descriptions, Titles and More to the New 23snaps Photobooks!</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/add-descriptions-titles-and-more-to-the-new-23snaps-photobooks/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2013 11:34:45 +0000</pubDate>

	<item>
				<title>Photo Editing and Management on Google+ Photos</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/photo-editing-and-management-on-google-photos/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 11 Nov 2013 12:00:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095972</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Yes, we're still banging on about Google+ photo editing and management ... it really is that good!

We've already explained (in great detail) about all of the fabulous photo editing tools that you have access to on Google+, we even broke it down in to 3 utterly digestible parts - if you haven't read them yet you can do so now: <strong><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-basic-adjustments/">Part 1</a></strong>, <strong><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-creative-adjustments/">Part 2</a></strong> &amp; <strong><a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/google-photo-editing-tool-picassa-23snaps/">Part 3</a></strong>.

But Google+ also offer brilliant photo management features, which we don't want you to miss.

We're sure that you're going to want to take full advantage of all of the editing and management features available to you, which means you'll want to make the most of the free storage quota that you get with Google+, so be aware that you<strong> have full control over whether your uploaded photos are stored at a standard size or full size print quality</strong>, which uses more storage space. If you don't make any adjustments to your settings, your photos will automatically be uploaded at their full size, rather than the standard size of 2048 pixels on the longest edge. You can upload an unlimited amount of standard size photos, but full size photos will count against your Google Drive storage quota, of which you get 15gb for free. To make the most of your Google+ drive, <strong>we'd recommend uploading all of your photos in the standard size, and then picking just your favorites to re-upload at a higher quality</strong> (FYI, the standard size is still pretty good quality!)

If you want to switch between the settings, all you have to do is select <img alt="" src="https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/SNP_09033CC5D017EE62507337A18C41B8CAAD6E_2715327_en_v4" width="16" height="16" /> <em>Settings</em> from your Google+ navigation menu. Then scroll down to the <em>Photos</em> section and check or uncheck the box next to <strong>'</strong><em>Upload my photos at full size', </em>depending on your preference. You can change this option at any time. You can also see how much storage you have left directly beneath this setting.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Upload-Settings-1.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095973" alt="Google+ Upload Settings" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Upload-Settings-1.png" width="360" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Upload-Settings-21.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095998" style="margin-left: 10px;" alt="Google+ Upload Settings 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Upload-Settings-21-300x219.png" width="260" /></a>

&nbsp;

Another great feature for the happy snappers among us it <strong>Highlights</strong>. We all know that once the camera comes out it is all too easy to end up taking hundreds of photos that all look pretty much the same. Well, <strong>Highlights helps you find your very best photos by auto-curating the images you upload to Google+,</strong> it then de-emphasises duplicates, blurry images and poor exposures, and it instead <em>highlights</em> the photos you will likely care more about. The system can now analyze your images, which is what enables it to get rid of the blurry photos, duplicates and images with bad exposure - which it will try to fix. It also has the amazing ability to recognize good images that include things like places and landmarks, and it can even detect faces and see if people are smiling. What used to take hours of work, can now happen automatically in the cloud in a matter seconds.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Screen-Shot-2013-11-07-at-15.54.21.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095977" alt="Google+ Highlights" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Screen-Shot-2013-11-07-at-15.54.21.png" width="600" /></a>
You can easily find your highlighted photos by clicking on <em>Photos</em> in your Google+ navigation menu, then selecting the <em>Highlights</em> tab at the top of the screen.

&nbsp;

As we've already mentioned, Google+ will try to fix photos with poor exposure. They do this using one of their very newest features called <strong>Auto Enhance</strong>. Auto Enhance makes improvements to each photo you add by <strong>accentuating important details, fixing the resolution and generally making your images look as good as they possibly can</strong>.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Auto-Enhance.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095994" alt="Google+ Auto Enhance" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Auto-Enhance.png" width="600" /></a>
However, if you don't want Google+ tinkering with your photos, you can undo these change really simply just by turning of the Auto Enhance.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Auto-Enhance-2.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740095995" alt="Google+ Auto Enhance 2" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Auto-Enhance-2.png" width="300" /></a>

&nbsp;

Finally (and this is one of the hands-down BEST features that Google+ provides!) ... <strong>Auto Awesome</strong>! Auto Awesome creates fun new versions of your photos and videos. Your photos will be combined into short animations, wide panoramas, or merged into group shots where everyone looks good. You'll know when an Auto Awesome photo has been created by the <img alt="" src="https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/SNP_3130466_en_v1" width="24" height="24" /> icon. There's a whole variety of different amazing photo effects that you can take advantage of:
<ul>
	<li><strong>Eraser</strong> - If you take a sequence of 3 or more photos in front of a structure or landmark with movement in the background, Eraser will give you a photo with all the moving objects removed. It's helpful for those situations when you’re trying to get a great shot of a landmark or other crowded place, but want to avoid including all of the people in the background of your photo.</li>
	<li><strong>Action -</strong> Take a series of photos of someone moving (dancing, running, jumping) and Auto Awesome will merge them together into one action shot where you can see the full range of movements in a single image, capturing the movement in one captivating still.</li>
	<li><strong>Pano</strong> - If you've taken a series of photos with overlapping landscape views, Auto Awesome will stitch these photos together into a panoramic image.</li>
	<li><strong>HDR</strong> - High Dynamic Range is the process of taking multiple exposures of the same image. By merging these images together, your photos will achieve a greater range of shadows and light. Uploading three similar images at different exposures--low, medium, and high exposure--will create an HDR image for you.</li>
	<li><strong>Smile</strong> - If you've taken a few group photos, Auto Awesome will choose the best shots of each person in your image and merge them into one great looking photo.</li>
	<li><strong>Mix</strong> - If you've taken a series of portraits sharing similar background elements, Auto Awesome will compile these photos together into a photobooth style grid. Mix is meant to showcase portrait photos taken with similar backgrounds in time, so it works best with close-ups of faces.</li>
	<li><strong>Motion</strong> - If you've taken a series of photos in succession (at least 5), Auto Awesome will stitch these photos together into a short animation.</li>
</ul>
Here are a couple of super cute examples of the <strong>Motion</strong> feature and the <strong>Mix</strong> feature in action!

<img class="alignnone" alt="" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Bb2hUsIDzeA/Unzvcdge_1I/AAAAAAAAAYE/KwYzxOfOz0w/w419-h558-no/photo+17-MOTION.gif" width="250" />  <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Photo-Mix.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740096005" alt="Google+ Photo Mix" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Google+-Photo-Mix.jpg" width="360" /></a>

We're sure you'll love getting stuck into these <strong>awesome</strong> features, and if you find something new that we've not talked about ... be sure to let us know!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps Tip Of The Week: Editing or Deleting Photos Uploaded in a Batch</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-tip-of-the-week-editing-or-deleting-photos-uploaded-in-a-batch/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 08 Nov 2013 12:00:06 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740095982</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Sometimes you forget to add a tag, alter a date, or misspell a description, especially when you're uploading a lot of photos all at once, but you shouldn't have to have those imperfections in your otherwise perfect digital babybook.

Let us talk you through how to fix those mistakes, or if you want to start the post over ... delete it completely.

<strong>Editing </strong>

<em>On the website</em>

Locate the batch of photos you wish to edit on your Newsfeed and open the photo you want to edit. Click on the gear icon located on the far right side of the lightbox. Select the option to <em>Edit</em>, you will then be given the opportunity to edit your post. Make sure you click <i>Update Post</i> when you’re done to ensure the edits are made.

<img title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200176066/Image_1.1.png" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200176066/Image_1.1.png" alt="" width="210" /><img style="margin-left: 5px; margin-right: 5px;" title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200171148/image_2.png" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200171148/image_2.png" alt="" width="210" height="116" /><img title="Image: https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/3dwilvbqjns3zqq/?name=3.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/3dwilvbqjns3zqq/?name=3.jpg" alt="3.jpg" width="210" height="116" />

&nbsp;

<em>On the app</em>

Locate the batch of photos you wish to edit on your Newsfeed, and open the batch by tapping it. Locate the post you want to edit and tap on the more options icon underneath the image; <img title="Image: https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/5x27gE1W1-e5ojyXKcQbSMFouhXC1pFdbEQJ4i9LNWOyAIfyFKCWMfrPzHt_eztDkzSjI2sQACfWCotFAWi5_4DEAG-UXEaoRCx3sDNCyyxeMh4Xc-KS" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/5x27gE1W1-e5ojyXKcQbSMFouhXC1pFdbEQJ4i9LNWOyAIfyFKCWMfrPzHt_eztDkzSjI2sQACfWCotFAWi5_4DEAG-UXEaoRCx3sDNCyyxeMh4Xc-KS" alt="" width="23px;" height="18px;" />on iOS and <img title="Image: https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/vnt414jonti9utl/?name=Android+mopre+options+icon.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/vnt414jonti9utl/?name=Android+mopre+options+icon.jpg" alt="Android_mopre_options_icon.jpg" width="23" height="18" />  on Android. Select <em>Edit Activity</em>. You will then be returned to the details screen where you can alter the description, tags and date of your content. Once you've finished making your changes, tap <em>Update</em> to save them to your timeline.

<img style="margin-right: 5px;" title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200171158/photo_1.PNG" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200171158/photo_1.PNG" alt="" width="156" height="234" /> <img title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200152023/Edit_Content_iOS_-_1.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200152023/Edit_Content_iOS_-_1.jpg" alt="" width="156" /> <img title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200176106/photo_2.PNG" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200176106/photo_2.PNG" alt="" width="156" height="234" /> <img title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200152033/Edit_Content_iOS_-_3.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200152033/Edit_Content_iOS_-_3.jpg" alt="" width="156" height="234" />

&nbsp;

<strong>Deleting</strong>

<em>On the website</em>

Locate the batch of photos, that contains the photo you want to delete, on your Newsfeed and open the photo you want to remove. Click on the gear icon located on the far right side of the lightbox. Select the option to <em>Delete</em> and then click the <em>OK</em> button to delete the content permanently.

<img title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200176066/Image_1.1.png" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200176066/Image_1.1.png" alt="" width="210" /><img title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200260183/Screen_Shot_2013-11-06_at_10.03.27.png" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200260183/Screen_Shot_2013-11-06_at_10.03.27.png" alt="" width="210" height="116" /><img title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200178966/Screen_Shot_2013-11-06_at_10.03.27.2.png" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200178966/Screen_Shot_2013-11-06_at_10.03.27.2.png" alt="" width="210" />

<em>On the app</em>

Locate the batch of photos, containing the image you want to delete, on your Newsfeed, and open the batch by tapping it. Locate the post you want to remove and tap on the more options icon underneath the image; <img title="Image: https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/5x27gE1W1-e5ojyXKcQbSMFouhXC1pFdbEQJ4i9LNWOyAIfyFKCWMfrPzHt_eztDkzSjI2sQACfWCotFAWi5_4DEAG-UXEaoRCx3sDNCyyxeMh4Xc-KS" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/5x27gE1W1-e5ojyXKcQbSMFouhXC1pFdbEQJ4i9LNWOyAIfyFKCWMfrPzHt_eztDkzSjI2sQACfWCotFAWi5_4DEAG-UXEaoRCx3sDNCyyxeMh4Xc-KS" alt="" width="23px;" height="18px;" />on iOS and <img title="Image: https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/vnt414jonti9utl/?name=Android+mopre+options+icon.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/vnt414jonti9utl/?name=Android+mopre+options+icon.jpg" alt="Android_mopre_options_icon.jpg" width="23" height="18" />  on Android. Select <em>Delete</em>. You will be asked to confirm whether you wish to delete the photo.

<strong><img style="margin-right: 5px;" title="Image: /hc/en-us/article_attachments/200260553/photo_1__1_.PNG" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/200260553/photo_1__1_.PNG" alt="" width="156" height="234" /> <img title="Image: https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/8yfgyzbkrzasxha/?name=Deleting+a+post+-+iOS+1.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/8yfgyzbkrzasxha/?name=Deleting+a+post+-+iOS+1.jpg" alt="Deleting_a_post_-_iOS_1.jpg" width="156" /> <img title="Image: https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/5atiyp8plyyg8at/?name=Deleting+a+post+-+iOS+2.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/5atiyp8plyyg8at/?name=Deleting+a+post+-+iOS+2.jpg" alt="Deleting_a_post_-_iOS_2.jpg" width="156" height="234" /> <img title="Image: https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/dvqewsf63tq1tvx/?name=Deleting+a+post+-+iOS+3.jpg" src="https://23snaps.zendesk.com/attachments/token/dvqewsf63tq1tvx/?name=Deleting+a+post+-+iOS+3.jpg" alt="Deleting_a_post_-_iOS_3.jpg" width="156" /></strong>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>23snaps Tip of The Week: Introducing the iOS7 Re-design</title>
		<link>http://blog.23snaps.com/23snaps-tip-of-the-week-introducing-the-ios7-re-design/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 15 Nov 2013 15:00:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.23snaps.com/?p=39740096023</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[23snaps has been completely redesigned for iOS7, our newest update features a <strong>sleek new interface</strong> that makes it even easier to use the features you know and love.

<a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-1-3.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740096031" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-1-3-169x300.png" alt="23snaps New Interface" width="155" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-2-2.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740096028" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-2-2-169x300.png" alt="23snaps New Interface" width="155" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-4.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740096030" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-4-169x300.png" alt="23snaps New Interface" width="155" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-3-1.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740096029" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-3-1-169x300.png" alt="23snaps New Interface" width="155" /></a>

You can now <strong>swipe to view the next image in your News Feed</strong> when in full screen mode. Tap on any update in your News Feed to enter full screen mode then swipe to enjoy all of your 23snaps content.

We're also very pleased to be introducing the <strong>Family Feed</strong>. You can now see all of your updates, the photos your children are tagged in, and the updates your partner has added in a single stream. Browse your updates in a timeline, calendar or gallery view. Switch easily into a filtered feed for any member of your family, or the families you are connected to.

<img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740096025" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-2-1-169x300.png" alt="23snaps Family Feed" width="210" /> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-3.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740096024" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-3-169x300.png" alt="23snaps Family Feed 1" width="210" /></a> <a href="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-1-2.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-39740096026" src="http://blog.23snaps.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/photo-1-2-169x300.png" alt="23snaps Family Feed" width="210" /></a>

To get all of these amazing features, <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/gb/app/23snaps-family-journal-private/id526481189?mt=8">download the latest update</a> now!]]></content:encoded>
